=begin
  grinsawl.lic  --  A Friendly Grinsawl Assistant

  Select the creature you want, and it attempts to capture the
  creature to build a stock of unfoiled cards, then foils them until one reaches your
  chosen tier (it accepts that tier or anything better).

  An in-game window is the control panel. From it you pick the target creature
  and the foil goal, watch your capture and foil cooldowns and your collection, and
  manage your tome: scan it, store finished cards into it, and pull a filed card
  back to your hand when you want it.

  [Organize tome] opens a separate window where you arrange your filed cards into
  the exact leaf/slot layout you want, then sends the moves to the game.

  USAGE
    ;grinsawl                                    open the control panel
    ;grinsawl <bronze|silver|gold> <creature>    set a goal and start at once
    ;k grinsawl                                  stop

  FIRST-TIME SETUP
    Click [Setup] in the window, then hold the bag you keep loose cards in, then your
    tome, clicking to assign each. They are remembered by name between sessions. Your
    Collector vissi must be slotted in both your aversaris and vangaris arcarium.

  WHAT'S NEW (v0.5.16)
    - Foil shorthand behind every creature name, unified across Target, Collection,
      and Retrieve: Gold/Silver/Bronze/White as G/S/B/W, e.g. "Kobold (2G|1S|3W)"
      (White = unfoiled). The Collection header shows your whole-collection total.
    - Creatures in your room that you already own a gold of now stay listed and are
      flagged DONE, so you can see at a glance not to bother capturing them.
    - Capture/foil no longer bounce off roundtime: grinsawl waits out your roundtime
      (including the disabling spell's cast time) before activating, and retries
      instead of giving up when an attempt doesn't fire.
    - Throwing a card updates your collection live -- grinsawl watches for cards you
      discard, so ;grinsawl clean no longer needs a rescan to refresh the counts.
    - The full Collection and Retrieve lists are shown now (no longer capped at a
      handful); collapse either with its [-] / [+] toggle.
    - Tidier: the goal's Start/Stop button is centered on its own line so long names
      can't push it off-screen, and reloading no longer spams Ruby warnings.

  EARLIER HIGHLIGHTS
    - Goal line has [Start] / [Stop] (Stop pauses but keeps your target); a "Cap only"
      foil goal that captures without ever foiling; "Bad foils" byproduct count.
    - Cleaner control panel + Setup: inline toggles/removes/steppers, assign or clear
      your card container and card book from their rows, not-standing pause toggle.
    - Safety holds: pause when not standing or when too many monsters are in the room;
      respect other players' claims; stay with a resisted "battle of wills".
    - Quiet by default; target list shows hostile mobs only, room creatures first.
    - Disabling spell (INCANT, e.g. 709); ;grinsawl clean to THROW bronze/silver one at
      a time; "Rescan for cards" rebuilds from your tome AND your card pack.
    - Tome organizer: arrange filed cards into the exact layout you want; foiling can
      pull an unfoiled card out of the tome; tome tier auto-detected.
    - Works around whatever you are holding; never targets corpses; pauses while you are
      dead; remembers your goal between sessions.

  author: Zedarius
  version: 0.5.16
=end

# Lich reopens this script's modules on every reload, so redefining our constants
# would spam "already initialized constant" warnings. Quiet just our own load (the
# constants still take fresh values), then restore $VERBOSE before anything runs.
$grinsawl_prior_verbose = $VERBOSE
$VERBOSE = nil

module Grinsawl
  VERSION = '0.5.16'

  TIER_RANK  = { bronze: 1, silver: 2, gold: 3 }.freeze
  ACTIVATORS = %w[rub tap push pull poke].freeze

  module Tier
    module_function

    def normalize(t)
      return nil if t.nil?

      s = t.to_s.strip.downcase.to_sym
      return :cap if s == :cap # capture-only goal (no foiling); ranks below any foil

      TIER_RANK.key?(s) ? s : nil
    end

    def rank(t)
      TIER_RANK[normalize(t)] || 0
    end

    # actual foil meets/exceeds the minimum acceptable foil (and is actually a foil)
    def meets?(actual, minimum)
      rank(actual).positive? && rank(actual) >= rank(minimum)
    end
  end

  module Parse
    module_function

    # A Collector vissi row inside an arcarium ANALYZE table, e.g.
    #   "     Collector       Primal      tap      3    Abilities: While holding..."
    # An arcarium can slot several activatable vissi, so we key on the Collector row.
    COLLECTOR_ROW = /^\s*Collector\s+\S+\s+(rub|tap|push|pull|poke)\s+(\d+)\s+Abilities:/i

    def clean_creature(raw)
      raw.to_s.sub(/\A(?:an?|the|some)\s+/i, '').strip.downcase
    end

    # Arcarium ANALYZE -> { verb:, tier:, cooldown:, active: } or nil (no Collector).
    def analyze_collector(lines)
      arr = Array(lines).map(&:to_s)
      idx = arr.index { |l| l =~ COLLECTOR_ROW }
      return nil unless idx

      m = COLLECTOR_ROW.match(arr[idx])
      cooldown = nil
      arr[(idx + 1)..].to_a.each do |l|
        if (cm = l.match(/(\d+)\s+second cooldown/i))
          cooldown = cm[1].to_i
          break
        end
      end
      active = arr.any? { |l| l =~ /currently in the active state/i } &&
               arr.none?  { |l| l =~ /currently in the inert state/i }
      { verb: m[1].downcase, tier: m[2].to_i, cooldown: cooldown, active: active }
    end

    # LOOK at a grinsawl -> { creature:, foil: nil|:bronze|:silver|:gold } or nil.
    def card(lines)
      text = Array(lines).map(&:to_s).join(' ')
      return nil unless text =~ /grinsawl/i

      creature = nil
      # Canonical card LOOK names the creature in its inscription ("A Grub from ...").
      if (m = text.match(/reads,\s*["']?\s*(?:an?\s+)?(.+?)\s+from\s+/i))
        creature = clean_creature(m[1])
      elsif (m = text.match(/bearing the image of\s+(.+?)\s*\./i))
        creature = clean_creature(m[1])
      end
      # Foiled card: "luxuriant <tier> foil" (in a leaf / capture) OR a loose card's
      # name/look "radiant <tier> grinsawl" ("radiant white grinsawl" = unfoiled).
      foil = if (fm = text.match(/luxuriant\s+(bronze|silver|gold)\s+foil/i)) then fm[1].downcase.to_sym
             elsif (fm = text.match(/radiant\s+(bronze|silver|gold)\s+grinsawl/i)) then fm[1].downcase.to_sym
             end
      { creature: creature, foil: foil }
    end

    # A grinsawl you THREW away -> { creature:, foil: } (white = unfoiled), else nil.
    # e.g. "Uninterested in a radiant silver grinsawl bearing the image of a bloody
    # halfling cannibal, you cast it aside." Lets clean drop it from the cache live,
    # no rescan needed. Strips any XML tags around the name first.
    def discard(line)
      s = line.to_s.gsub(/<[^>]+>/, '')
      m = s.match(/radiant\s+(white|bronze|silver|gold)\s+grinsawl bearing the image of\s+(.+?),?\s+you cast it aside/i) or return nil

      { creature: Match.normalize(m[2]), foil: (m[1].downcase == 'white' ? nil : m[1].downcase.to_sym) }
    end

    # Capture attempt terminal line -> { creature: } on success, :fail, else nil.
    # :fail includes a BROKEN link (creature retreated / you acted): "maintaining the
    # tether becomes impossible ... the radiance fades into nothingness".
    def capture_result(line)
      s = line.to_s
      if (m = s.match(/solidifies into a radiant white grinsawl bearing the image of\s+(.+?)\./i))
        return { creature: clean_creature(m[1]) }
      end
      return :fail if s =~ /failed card capture|the (?:magical )?link (?:fades|expires|dissipates|is broken)|fail(?:s|ed) to (?:capture|imprint|link)|tether (?:becomes impossible|untwines)|radiance fades into nothingness|too much distance between you/i

      nil
    end

    # Foil attempt terminal line -> { tier: } on success, :mismatch, :broke, else nil.
    # :broke is the link breaking ("...leaving your grinsawl unharmed" / tether untwines).
    def foil_result(line)
      s = line.to_s
      if (m = s.match(/your card now bears a luxuriant\s+(bronze|silver|gold)\s+foil/i))
        return { tier: m[1].downcase.to_sym }
      end
      return :mismatch if s =~ /only attempt to foil this grinsawl by establishing a link with an identical creature/i
      return :broke if s =~ /tether (?:becomes impossible|untwines)|too much distance between you|leaving your grinsawl unharmed/i

      nil
    end

    # ANALYZE <tome> -> { tier:, leaves:, cap: } from "The <noun> is tier N, it can hold L
    # leaves, and each slot can hold C duplicate grinsawl." cap is the exact per-slot stack
    # (tier1 1, tier2 5, tier3 20). nil if the line isn't present.
    def tome_tier(lines)
      text = Array(lines).map(&:to_s).join(' ')
      cap = text[/each slot can hold\s+(\d+)\s+duplicate grinsawl/i, 1]
      return nil unless cap

      { tier: text[/\bis tier\s+(\d+)/i, 1]&.to_i,
        leaves: text[/can hold\s+(\d+)\s+leaves/i, 1]&.to_i,
        cap: cap.to_i }
    end
  end

  module Match
    module_function

    def normalize(name)
      name.to_s.sub(/\A(?:an?|the|some)\s+/i, '').strip.downcase
    end

    # A room is "contested" when the Claim module is available and reports the
    # room is NOT ours (a non-grouped player is present). Pure decision; the
    # runtime supplies available/mine from Lich::Claim, matching creaturewindow.
    def room_contested?(available:, mine:)
      available && !mine
    end

    # Foiling requires an IDENTICAL creature: full depicted-name match
    # ("big ugly kobold" != "kobold").
    def identical?(card_creature, present_creature)
      a = normalize(card_creature)
      !a.empty? && a == normalize(present_creature)
    end

    # The goal label may be a partial/base name: "hinterboar" should match the
    # in-game "gold-bristled hinterboar". Used to pick what to CAPTURE and which
    # cards count toward the goal (foiling itself still needs identical?).
    def goal_match?(goal_creature, name)
      g = normalize(goal_creature)
      !g.empty? && normalize(name).include?(g)
    end

    def wanted?(creature, want, avoid)
      c = normalize(creature)
      return false if Array(avoid).any? { |a| !a.to_s.strip.empty? && c.include?(normalize(a)) }

      w = Array(want).reject { |x| x.to_s.strip.empty? }
      return true if w.empty?

      w.any? { |x| c.include?(normalize(x)) }
    end
  end

  module Planner
    module_function

    # state: { goal:{creature,min}, present:[names], unfoiled_creatures:[names],
    #          stock:Int, aversaris_ready:Bool, vangaris_ready:Bool, buffer:Int }
    # Foil takes priority (it is the scarce, goal-advancing step).
    # => [:foil, present_name] | [:capture, present_name] | :idle
    def next_action(state)
      goal     = state[:goal] || {}
      present  = Array(state[:present])
      unfoiled = Array(state[:unfoiled_creatures])

      # FOIL: a present creature IDENTICAL to one of our unfoiled goal cards.
      # Skipped entirely in capture-only mode (goal min :cap) -- we keep the captures.
      if state[:vangaris_ready] && goal[:min] != :cap
        p = present.find { |name| unfoiled.any? { |cc| Match.identical?(cc, name) } }
        return [:foil, p] if p
      end
      # CAPTURE: a present creature matching the goal, while backlog below buffer.
      if state[:aversaris_ready] && state[:stock].to_i < state[:buffer].to_i
        p = present.find { |name| Match.goal_match?(goal[:creature], name) }
        return [:capture, p] if p
      end
      :idle
    end
  end

  # Group ledger entries (each { creature:, foil: }) into per-creature counts for
  # the status window. => { "kobold" => { unfoiled:, bronze:, silver:, gold: }, ... }
  module Summary
    module_function

    def by_creature(entries)
      out = {}
      Array(entries).each do |e|
        c = e[:creature].to_s.strip
        next if c.empty?

        h = (out[c] ||= { unfoiled: 0, bronze: 0, silver: 0, gold: 0 })
        key = e[:foil].nil? ? :unfoiled : e[:foil].to_s.to_sym
        h[key] += 1 if h.key?(key)
      end
      out
    end

    # Compact foil shorthand shown after a creature name, unified across the panel.
    # The four grinsawl colors: Gold/Silver/Bronze/White (White = unfoiled, as the
    # game's own "radiant white grinsawl"). G/S/B/W, non-zero only, e.g. "(2G|1S|1W)".
    # Returns "" when there are no cards. Accepts a counts hash with any of
    # :gold/:silver/:bronze/:unfoiled.
    def foil_tag(counts)
      counts ||= {}
      parts = []
      parts << "#{counts[:gold].to_i}G"     if counts[:gold].to_i.positive?
      parts << "#{counts[:silver].to_i}S"   if counts[:silver].to_i.positive?
      parts << "#{counts[:bronze].to_i}B"   if counts[:bronze].to_i.positive?
      parts << "#{counts[:unfoiled].to_i}W" if counts[:unfoiled].to_i.positive?
      parts.empty? ? '' : "(#{parts.join('|')})"
    end

    # Candidate targets for the control panel: creatures present in the room UNION
    # creatures already tracked, filtered by want/avoid, each with its counts.
    # A creature you already own a GOLD of is dropped -- gold is the top tier, so it
    # is done and not worth suggesting as a target.
    #
    # Sort: creatures IN THE ROOM first, ordered by most unfoiled cards available
    # (a mob with 6 unfoiled on top, then 3, then 0-but-here); then creatures NOT
    # in the room, ordered by how many FOILED cards you already have (descending).
    # => [{ creature:, unfoiled:, foiled:, total:, in_room: }].
    def target_candidates(present, entries, want = [], avoid = [])
      counts = by_creature(entries)
      here   = Array(present).map { |n| n.to_s.strip }.reject(&:empty?)
      names  = (here + counts.keys).map { |n| n.to_s.strip }.reject(&:empty?).uniq
      # Keep creatures IN THE ROOM even when you already own a gold (flagged "done"
      # so you can see at a glance not to bother); only hide golded creatures that
      # aren't present, to keep the tracked tail uncluttered.
      names.select { |n| Match.wanted?(n, want, avoid) && (here.include?(n) || (counts[n] || {})[:gold].to_i.zero?) }
           .map do |n|
             h = counts[n] || {}
             total = h.values.sum
             unfoiled = h[:unfoiled].to_i
             { creature: n, unfoiled: unfoiled, foiled: total - unfoiled, total: total,
               in_room: here.include?(n), counts: h, done: h[:gold].to_i.positive? }
           end
           # In-room first; within it, not-done before done, then most unfoiled. Then the
           # tracked tail by most foiled.
           .sort_by { |c| c[:in_room] ? [0, c[:done] ? 1 : 0, -c[:unfoiled], c[:creature]] : [1, -c[:foiled], c[:creature]] }
    end

    # Merge sack ledger {id=>{creature,foil}} and tome cards [{id,creature,foil,qty}]
    # into {creature,foil} entries, deduped by exist-id (a card in both is counted
    # once -- sack wins) and qty-expanded for stacked tome slots.
    def dedup_inventory(ledger_hash, tome_cards)
      seen = {}
      entries = []
      (ledger_hash || {}).each do |id, info|
        seen[id.to_s] = true
        entries << { creature: info[:creature], foil: info[:foil] }
      end
      Array(tome_cards).each do |c|
        key = c[:id].to_s
        next if !key.empty? && seen[key]

        seen[key] = true unless key.empty?
        [c[:qty].to_i, 1].max.times { entries << { creature: c[:creature], foil: c[:foil] } }
      end
      entries
    end

    # Collapse tome cards into clickable retrieve groups: distinct (creature, foil)
    # with a summed qty. => [{creature:, foil:, qty:}] sorted by name then tier desc.
    def group_tome(tome_cards)
      groups = {}
      Array(tome_cards).each do |c|
        cre = c[:creature].to_s.strip
        next if cre.empty?

        key = [cre, c[:foil]]
        groups[key] = (groups[key] || 0) + [c[:qty].to_i, 1].max
      end
      groups.map { |(cre, foil), qty| { creature: cre, foil: foil, qty: qty } }
            .sort_by { |g| [g[:creature], -Tier.rank(g[:foil])] }
    end

    # Choose the single tome card to retrieve. Matches creature by exact depicted
    # name first, then partial (so "kobold" finds "a big ugly kobold"); filters by an
    # explicit tier or the unfoiled flag; otherwise prefers the highest tier present.
    # => one card hash or nil.
    def pick_card(tome_cards, creature, tier: nil, unfoiled: false)
      cre  = Match.normalize(creature)
      cand = Array(tome_cards).select do |c|
        name = c[:creature].to_s
        Match.normalize(name) == cre || Match.goal_match?(cre, name)
      end
      cand = cand.select { |c| c[:foil].nil? } if unfoiled
      cand = cand.select { |c| c[:foil] == tier } if tier
      cand.min_by { |c| [(Match.normalize(c[:creature].to_s) == cre ? 0 : 1), -Tier.rank(c[:foil])] }
    end

    # Find a configured item in a pool of {id:, name:} hashes. Item exist-ids change
    # across logins, so we match by saved id first, then by NAME -- and tolerantly,
    # since the saved name can drift (saved "bear hide pack" must still find a live
    # "black bear hide pack"): exact, then either name containing the other.
    # => the matched hash or nil.
    def resolve_item(pool, id, name)
      pool = Array(pool)
      nm = name.to_s.strip.downcase
      found = nil
      found = pool.find { |o| o[:id].to_s == id.to_s } if id && !id.to_s.empty?
      unless found || nm.empty?
        found = pool.find { |o| o[:name].to_s.strip.casecmp?(nm) } ||
                pool.find { |o| o[:name].to_s.downcase.include?(nm) } ||
                pool.find { |o| (n = o[:name].to_s.strip.downcase); !n.empty? && nm.include?(n) }
      end
      found
    end

    # Decide where to file a card of (creature, foil) given a live slot model: a list
    # of { leaf:, slot:, card: nil|{creature,foil,qty} }. Cards stack onto a slot with
    # the IDENTICAL depicted name and SAME foil that still has room (qty < cap); else
    # the lowest empty slot is used. Both pick the LOWEST [leaf, slot] so the tome fills
    # from leaf 1 forward regardless of which leaf the book happens to be open to.
    # => { leaf:, slot:, mode: :stack|:empty } or nil (full).
    # `taken` is a list of [leaf, slot] already filled THIS batch -- a safety net so a
    # second card can never be sent to a slot we just put a (different) card in, even if
    # the in-memory model didn't reflect the prior fill. Stacking onto a matching slot is
    # still allowed (same creature+foil), since that's a legitimate duplicate.
    def place_card(model, creature, foil, cap: 2, taken: [])
      cre = Match.normalize(creature)
      order = ->(e) { [e[:leaf].to_i.zero? ? 99 : e[:leaf].to_i, e[:slot].to_i] }
      stack = Array(model).select do |e|
        c = e[:card]
        c && Match.normalize(c[:creature]) == cre && c[:foil] == foil && c[:qty].to_i < cap
      end.min_by(&order)
      return { leaf: stack[:leaf], slot: stack[:slot], mode: :stack } if stack

      used = Array(taken).map { |l, s| [l.to_i, s.to_i] }
      empty = Array(model).select { |e| e[:card].nil? && !used.include?([e[:leaf].to_i, e[:slot].to_i]) }.min_by(&order)
      empty ? { leaf: empty[:leaf], slot: empty[:slot], mode: :empty } : nil
    end
  end

  # Tome reading: parse a verbose leaf into 12 slots. Mirrors reorder-spellbook's
  # Parser/Scanner split. Pure (unit-tested against a real grimoire_capture fixture).
  module Tome
    DATE_RX  = /\b\w{3}\s+\w{3}\s+\d{1,2}\s+\d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2}\s+ET\b/.freeze
    # The foil banner: GOLD renders as "** Gold **" but SILVER/BRONZE render bare ("Silver"
    # / "Bronze") -- so the asterisks are optional. Safe for the grid banner row (tiers only).
    TIER_RX  = /(?:\*\*\s*)?(Gold|Silver|Bronze)(?:\s*\*\*)?/i.freeze
    QTY_RX   = /\bQty\s+(\d+)\b/.freeze
    ORDINALS = %w[first second third fourth fifth sixth seventh eighth ninth tenth eleventh twelfth].freeze

    module_function

    # Walk a raw leaf line -> [stripped, anchors[[off,exist,text]], taps[[off,slot_n]]].
    # Captures each anchor/empty-tap's char offset in the STRIPPED text so we can
    # place it in one of the leaf's 4 columns.
    def scan_line(raw)
      raw = raw.to_s
      s = +''
      anchors = []
      taps = []
      i = 0
      while i < raw.length
        if raw[i] == '<'
          close = raw.index('>', i) or break
          tag = raw[i..close]
          if (m = tag.match(/\A<a\s+exist="([^"]+)"/))
            endtag = raw.index('</a>', close + 1) or break
            text = raw[(close + 1)...endtag]
            anchors << [s.length, m[1], text]
            s << text
            i = endtag + 4
          elsif (m = tag.match(/\A<d\s+cmd="tap\s+#\d+\s+at\s+(\d+)"/))
            endtag = raw.index('</d>', close + 1) or break
            text = raw[(close + 1)...endtag]
            taps << [s.length, m[1].to_i]
            s << text
            i = endtag + 4
          else
            i = close + 1
          end
        else
          s << raw[i]
          i += 1
        end
      end
      [s, anchors, taps]
    end

    def col_of(offset, textlen, width)
      w = width / 4.0
      [[((offset + (textlen / 2.0)) / w).floor, 0].max, 3].min
    end

    # Parse a leaf into { slots: [s1..s12] }, each nil (empty) or
    # { slot:, id:, creature:, foil: nil|:bronze|:silver|:gold, qty: }. Handles BOTH
    # TILT display modes: a numbered list and the 4-column grid.
    def leaf(lines)
      Array(lines).any? { |l| l.to_s =~ /^\s*\d+\.\s/ } ? leaf_list(lines) : leaf_grid(lines)
    end

    # Numbered-list leaf (post-TILT): one line per slot, slot number explicit, foil
    # and qty inline -- e.g. "  1. ** Gold ** a slimy little grub (1) <date> <loc>"
    # or "  5. (blank)".
    def leaf_list(lines)
      slots = {}
      Array(lines).each do |raw|
        m = raw.to_s.match(/^\s*(\d+)\.\s+(.*)$/) or next
        n = m[1].to_i
        next unless n.between?(1, 12)

        rest = m[2]
        stripped = rest.gsub(/<[^>]+>/, '')
        if stripped =~ /\(blank\)/i || stripped.strip.empty?
          slots[n] = nil
          next
        end
        anchors = rest.scan(/<a\s+[^>]*\bexist="([^"]+)"[^>]*>([^<]*)<\/a>/)
        name = anchors.map { |(_e, t)| t }.join(' ').strip
        # The foil tier (if any) sits BEFORE the creature anchor; gold is "** Gold **",
        # silver/bronze are bare. Read it from that prefix only, anchored at the start, so
        # a creature name like "silver-scaled" can never be mistaken for a foil.
        prefix = (rest[/\A(.*?)<a\s/im, 1] || rest).gsub(/<[^>]+>/, '')
        foil = prefix[/\A\s*(?:\*\*\s*)?(gold|silver|bronze)\b/i, 1]&.downcase&.to_sym
        name = stripped.sub(/\A\s*(?:\*\*\s*)?(?:gold|silver|bronze)\b\s*(?:\*\*\s*)?/i, '').sub(/\(\d+\).*/m, '').strip if name.empty?
        qty  = (qm = stripped.match(/\((\d+)\)/)) ? qm[1].to_i : 1
        slots[n] = { slot: n, id: anchors.first&.first, creature: Match.normalize(name), foil: foil, qty: qty }
      end
      { slots: (1..12).map { |n| slots[n] } }
    end

    # 4-column grid leaf: occupied slots anchored to each super-row's date line
    # (banner 3 lines above, article 2, creature 1); foil/qty read by COLUMN.
    def leaf_grid(lines)
      scanned = Array(lines).map { |l| scan_line(l) }
      width = scanned.map { |sx, _, _| sx.length }.max.to_i
      width = 116 if width.zero?
      slots = {}
      scanned.each { |_sx, _a, taps| taps.each { |(_o, n)| slots[n] ||= nil } }

      date_idxs = scanned.each_index.select { |i| scanned[i][0] =~ DATE_RX }
      date_idxs.each_with_index do |d, band|
        next if d < 2

        cre = scanned[d - 1]
        art = scanned[d - 2]
        ban = scanned[d - 3] || ['', [], []]
        qline = scanned[(d + 1)..].to_a.find { |sx, _, _| sx =~ QTY_RX } || ['', [], []]

        foil_col = {}
        ban[0].to_s.scan(TIER_RX) { foil_col[col_of(Regexp.last_match.begin(0), Regexp.last_match[0].length, width)] = Regexp.last_match[1].downcase.to_sym }
        qty_col = {}
        qline[0].to_s.scan(QTY_RX) { qty_col[col_of(Regexp.last_match.begin(0), Regexp.last_match[0].length, width)] = Regexp.last_match[1].to_i }

        cre[1].each do |(off, exist, text)|
          c = col_of(off, text.length, width)
          article = (art[1].find { |(_o, e, _t)| e == exist } || [])[2]
          n = (band * 4) + c + 1
          slots[n] = { slot: n, id: exist, creature: Match.normalize("#{article} #{text}"),
                       foil: foil_col[c], qty: (qty_col[c] || 1) }
        end
      end
      { slots: (1..12).map { |n| slots[n] } }
    end

    # First empty slot number (1..12) on a parsed leaf, or nil if the leaf is full.
    def first_empty_slot(leaf_result)
      slots = (leaf_result.is_a?(Hash) ? leaf_result[:slots] : leaf_result) || []
      (1..12).find { |n| slots[n - 1].nil? }
    end

    # Leaf number from any flip/inspect message: the inspect header ("...the ledger's
    # first open leaf"), a flip arrival ("arrive at the second leaf"), the last-leaf land
    # ("land on the twelfth and last leaf"), or the wrap ("flip back to the first leaf").
    # nil otherwise. Lets goto_leaf read the leaf from FLIP responses (no per-step inspect).
    def flip_leaf(line)
      s = line.to_s
      m = s.match(/\b(\w+)\s+open\s+leaf\b/i) ||
          s.match(/arrive at the (\w+)\s+leaf\b/i) ||
          s.match(/land on the (\w+)\s+and last leaf\b/i) ||
          s.match(/flip back to the (\w+)\s+leaf\b/i)
      return nil unless m

      idx = ORDINALS.index(m[1].downcase)
      idx ? idx + 1 : nil
    end

    # Flavor-agnostic: a tier-2 tome's name/prose is user-customizable, so key on the
    # grinsawl-system phrasing, never the item name.
    def opened?(line)  = (line.to_s =~ /open leaf|is already open|ripple of crimson|easing the cover open|carefully flatten|You open a/i) ? true : false
    def stored?(line)  = (line.to_s =~ /grafted likeness remains/i) ? true : false

    # A retrieve's terminal line -> { creature:, foil: nil|:bronze|:silver|:gold } or nil.
    def retrieved?(line)
      m = line.to_s.match(/radiant\s+(?:(bronze|silver|gold)\s+)?(?:white\s+)?grinsawl bearing the image of\s+(.+?)\s+separates cleanly/i) or return nil
      { foil: (m[1] ? m[1].downcase.to_sym : nil), creature: Match.normalize(m[2]) }
    end

    # Organizer planner (pure). Turn a current tome layout into a target layout using the
    # sack as scratch: lift only the cards that are misplaced out to the sack, then file the
    # vacancies from the sack. Cards already of the right type in the right slot are left
    # untouched (fixed points). full:true ignores fixed points -- the bulletproof rebuild.
    #
    # Layouts are 0-indexed arrays: layout[leaf_i][slot_i] = list of 0-2 cards
    # { creature:, foil: }. Output uses 1-based leaf/slot to match the game:
    #   { pull: [[leaf, slot], ...],                          # one entry per card to lift out
    #     fill: [{ leaf:, slot:, creature:, foil: }, ...] }   # one per card to file, in order
    module Plan
      module_function

      def slot_at(layout, li, si)
        row = Array(layout)[li]
        row ? Array(row[si]) : []
      end

      def key(card) = [Match.normalize(card[:creature]), card[:foil]]

      def tally(cards)
        cards.each_with_object(Hash.new(0)) { |c, h| h[key(c)] += 1 }
      end

      def plan(current, target, full: false)
        pull = []
        fill = []
        nleaves = [Array(current).length, Array(target).length].max
        (0...nleaves).each do |li|
          (0...12).each do |si|
            cur = tally(slot_at(current, li, si))
            tgt = tally(slot_at(target, li, si))
            (cur.keys | tgt.keys).each do |k|
              fixed = full ? 0 : [cur[k], tgt[k]].min
              (cur[k] - fixed).times { pull << [li + 1, si + 1] }
              (tgt[k] - fixed).times { fill << { leaf: li + 1, slot: si + 1, creature: k[0], foil: k[1] } }
            end
          end
        end
        { pull: pull, fill: fill.sort_by { |f| [f[:leaf], f[:slot]] } }
      end
    end
  end

  def self.version
    VERSION
  end
end

# ------------------------------- runtime (Lich) -------------------------------
# This layer drives the live game; the pure modules above are unit-tested. The
# game I/O (exact failure/cooldown messages, hand juggling, sack/tome browsing)
# is a first cut meant to be tuned live -- see the `# LIVE:` notes.
if defined?(Script)
  begin
    require 'gtk3' # only the organizer needs it; the rest of grinsawl runs without GTK
  rescue LoadError, StandardError
    nil
  end

  module Grinsawl
    class << self
      attr_accessor :state, :goal, :ledger, :cooldowns
    end

    def self.boot
      self.ledger    = {}                         # card-id => { creature:, foil: }
      self.cooldowns = { aversaris: 0.0, vangaris: 0.0 }
      self.goal      = nil
      g = CharSettings['goal'] # restore last goal (idle until you click Go)
      self.goal = { creature: g[:creature].to_s, min: (Grinsawl::Tier.normalize(g[:min]) || :gold) } \
        if g.is_a?(Hash) && !g[:creature].to_s.strip.empty?
      self.state = {
        running: true, active: false, want: [], avoid: [], buffer: 3,
        byproducts: 0, view: :status, last_status: nil, config_dirty: false,
        cd_marks: { aversaris: [], vangaris: [] }, # cooldown milestones already announced
        discarded: Queue.new,                       # cards seen thrown away (DownstreamHook -> main loop)
        organizer: nil, org_open_request: false,   # GTK organizer window + open flag
        tome_cap: (CharSettings['tome_cap'] || 2).to_i, # stack per slot: tier1 2, tier2 5, tier3 20
        default_min: (CharSettings['default_min'] ? CharSettings['default_min'].to_s.to_sym : :gold),
        aversaris: nil, vangaris: nil,
        card_sack_id: CharSettings['card_sack_id'], card_sack_name: CharSettings['card_sack_name'],
        tome_id: CharSettings['tome_id'], tome_name: CharSettings['tome_name'],
        # plain copies of the mutable settings -- never hold a live SettingsProxy
        tome_cards: plain_array(CharSettings['tome_cards']) { |c| { leaf: c[:leaf], slot: c[:slot], creature: c[:creature], foil: c[:foil], qty: c[:qty], id: c[:id] } },
        tome_scanned_at: CharSettings['tome_scanned_at'],
        disable_spell: (CharSettings['disable_spell'] || '').to_s, # which spell to cast on the target first
        disable_enabled: (CharSettings['disable_enabled'] ? true : false), # whether to cast it at all
        pause_list: (pl = plain_array(CharSettings['pause_list']) { |x| x.to_s }).empty? ? %w[energywings spellactive] : pl,
        max_mobs: (CharSettings['max_mobs'] || 0).to_i, # pause if MORE than this many monsters are in the room (0 = off)
        respect_claims: (CharSettings['respect_claims'].nil? ? true : (CharSettings['respect_claims'] ? true : false)), # hold when another hunter has claimed the room (default on)
        fold_collection: (CharSettings['fold_collection'] ? true : false), # collapse the Collection list in the panel
        fold_retrieve: (CharSettings['fold_retrieve'] ? true : false),     # collapse the Retrieve list in the panel
        pause_not_standing: (CharSettings['pause_not_standing'].nil? ? true : (CharSettings['pause_not_standing'] ? true : false)), # hold when not standing (default on)
        paused_reason: nil                              # last auto-pause reason announced (edge-triggered, no spam)
      }
    end

    # ---- small helpers ----
    def self.strip(lines)
      Array(lines).map { |l| l.to_s.gsub(/<[^>]+>/, '').rstrip }
    end

    # CharSettings returns Lich SettingsProxy objects; mutating one in place (push/delete/
    # []=) or assigning it back raises (private rebind_to_live!). Copy to a PLAIN array on
    # read -- via .each/[] which the proxy reliably delegates -- so we own the data.
    def self.plain_array(v)
      out = []
      (v || []).each { |e| out << (block_given? ? yield(e) : e) }
      out
    rescue StandardError
      []
    end

    # Configured containers, resolved by id with a name fallback (re-saving the id
    # when Lich remaps it, like markscrolls' resolve_container).
    def self.resolve_role(role)
      idk = "#{role}_id".to_sym
      nmk = "#{role}_name".to_sym
      # Search worn inventory, BOTH hands, and inside known containers -- a tome is
      # often kept in a pack and only pulled to hand to use, and neither hands nor
      # pack contents live in GameObj.inv.
      contained = (GameObj.containers.values.flatten rescue [])
      pool = (GameObj.inv.to_a + [GameObj.right_hand, GameObj.left_hand] + contained)
             .compact.select { |o| o.id }.uniq(&:id)
      simple = pool.map { |o| { id: o.id, name: o.name, obj: o } }
      match = Summary.resolve_item(simple, state[idk], state[nmk])
      obj = match && match[:obj]
      if obj && obj.id.to_s != state[idk].to_s
        state[idk] = obj.id.to_s     # refresh id from the remembered name (ids change across logins)
        state[:config_dirty] = true  # main loop persists; CharSettings needs the script thread
      end
      obj
    end

    def self.card_sack   = resolve_role('card_sack')
    def self.tome        = resolve_role('tome')
    def self.sack        = card_sack
    def self.configured? = !card_sack.nil?

    # Refer to the user's items by their real names ("bear hide pack", "amber gold
    # ledger"), not the generic words -- their sack is a pack, their tome a ledger.
    def self.sack_label = state[:card_sack_name] || 'card sack'
    def self.tome_label = state[:tome_name] || 'tome'

    def self.sack_contents
      s = card_sack
      s ? (GameObj.containers[s.id] || []).compact : []
    end

    # Lich only knows a container's contents after a LOOK inside; populate
    # GameObj.containers[sack] with a quiet `look in` (opening it first if closed).
    # MAIN-THREAD ONLY (issue_command needs a valid Script.current).
    def self.ensure_sack_loaded
      s = card_sack or return false
      look = tome_io("look in ##{s.id}", /In the|There (?:is|are)|nothing in|That is closed|You glance|empty|can't|don't/i)
      if strip(look).any? { |l| l =~ /That is closed/i }
        tome_io("open ##{s.id}", /You open|already open|can't|don't/i)
        tome_io("look in ##{s.id}", /In the|There (?:is|are)|nothing in|You glance|empty/i)
      end
      20.times { break if GameObj.containers[s.id].is_a?(Array); sleep 0.05 }
      GameObj.containers[s.id].is_a?(Array)
    end

    def self.find_inv(idstr)
      id = idstr.to_s.sub('#', '').strip
      GameObj.inv.to_a.compact.find { |o| o.id.to_s == id }
    end

    def self.held
      [GameObj.right_hand, GameObj.left_hand].compact.reject { |o| o.id.nil? }
    end

    def self.held_grinsawl
      held.find { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }
    end

    # The item in hand (right preferred), or nil. Powers "hold it and click" setup.
    def self.held_item
      r = GameObj.right_hand
      l = GameObj.left_hand
      (r && !r.id.nil? ? r : nil) || (l && !l.id.nil? ? l : nil)
    end

    def self.free_hand!
      return true if GameObj.right_hand.id.nil? || GameObj.left_hand.id.nil?

      g = held_grinsawl
      stow_to_sack(g.id) if g
      GameObj.right_hand.id.nil? || GameObj.left_hand.id.nil?
    end

    def self.stow_to_sack(id)
      s = sack or return false
      dothistimeout("put ##{id} in ##{s.id}", 5, /You put|already|no room|What were you/i)
      true
    end

    def self.get_from_sack(id)
      s = sack or return false
      dothistimeout("get ##{id} from ##{s.id}", 5, /You (?:get|pick up|remove)|already|What were you/i)
      held.any? { |o| o.id.to_s == id.to_s }
    end

    # The user's GEAR: anything held that isn't a grinsawl card or the tome -- a weapon,
    # shield, runestaff, orb, wand, anything. We set these aside (any noun) to free hands for
    # tome work and put them back after.
    def self.held_gear
      tid = (tome&.id).to_s
      held.reject { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i || (!tid.empty? && o.id.to_s == tid) }
    end

    def self.holding?(id) = held.any? { |o| o.id.to_s == id.to_s }
    def self.a_hand_free? = GameObj.right_hand.id.nil? || GameObj.left_hand.id.nil?

    # Put a held item away (the game's STOW routes weapon->sheath, runestaff->sling, misc->
    # stow container; fall back to the card sack) and remember it for restore_setaside.
    def self.set_aside(o)
      return if o.nil? || !holding?(o.id)

      dothistimeout("stow ##{o.id}", 4, /You (?:put|stow|sheathe|sling|hang|tuck|slip|strap)|already|no room|can't|don't|What were you/i)
      stow_to_sack(o.id) if holding?(o.id) # STOW didn't take -> use the card sack
      (state[:setaside] ||= []) << o.id.to_s unless holding?(o.id)
    end

    def self.set_aside_all_gear = held_gear.each { |o| set_aside(o) }

    # Return every set-aside item to hand (by id, from wherever it went).
    def self.restore_setaside
      Array(state[:setaside]).each do |id|
        dothistimeout("get ##{id}", 4, /You (?:get|pick up|remove|wield|sling|hold|grab|slip)|already|can't|don't|What were you/i)
      end
      state[:setaside] = []
    end

    # Put the tome away (we held it for the operation), so hands free up for the gear.
    def self.stow_tome(t)
      return unless t && holding?(t.id)

      dothistimeout("stow ##{t.id}", 4, /You (?:put|stow|tuck|hang|slip|strap)|already|no room|can't|don't|What were you/i)
      stow_to_sack(t.id) if holding?(t.id)
    end

    # Filing a card needs BOTH the ledger and the grinsawl in hand ("You must be holding
    # both the ledger and the grinsawl" otherwise). Navigation (open/inspect/flip) works
    # with the tome in a pack, but `tap`/`get` from it do not -- so pull the tome to a hand,
    # stowing a held grinsawl, then a held gear item if needed, to make room.
    def self.ensure_tome_in_hand(t)
      return true if holding?(t.id)

      held.select { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }.each { |o| stow_to_sack(o.id) }
      set_aside(held_gear.first) unless a_hand_free? # both hands full -> set a held item aside
      unless a_hand_free?
        respond "[grinsawl] both hands are full -- free one so I can hold your #{t.name}."
        return false
      end
      dothistimeout("get ##{t.id}", 5, /You (?:get|pick up|remove|sling|wield)|already (?:in|have)|in your|What were you/i)
      holding?(t.id)
    end

    # Free both hands of the user's gear, bring the tome to hand for the block, then put the
    # tome away and restore the gear -- hands return to how they were. The block keeps the
    # other hand free for the card. Used by EVERY tome op (store, organize, retrieve).
    def self.with_tome_hands(t)
      set_aside_all_gear
      ok = ensure_tome_in_hand(t)
      begin
        yield(ok)
      ensure
        stow_tome(t)
        restore_setaside
      end
    end

    # ---- analyze / setup ----
    def self.analyze_arcarium(which)
      return nil if dead?

      lines = Lich::Util.issue_command(
        "analyze my #{which} arcarium",
        /You analyze the/i, /<prompt/,
        include_end: false, timeout: 8, usexml: true, quiet: true, use_fput: false
      )
      Parse.analyze_collector(strip(lines))
    end

    # ANALYZE the tome to read its tier and the exact per-slot stack cap, then set the cap
    # (so the user never has to tell us). => the parsed info or nil.
    def self.detect_tome_tier
      return nil if dead?

      t = tome or return nil

      lines = Lich::Util.issue_command(
        "analyze ##{t.id}",
        /analyze|is tier \d+|duplicate grinsawl|can hold \d+ leaves/i, /<prompt/,
        include_end: false, timeout: 8, usexml: true, quiet: true, use_fput: false
      )
      info = Parse.tome_tier(strip(lines))
      return nil unless info && info[:cap]&.positive?

      state[:tome_cap] = info[:cap]
      state[:tome_leaves] = info[:leaves] if info[:leaves]
      state[:config_dirty] = true
      respond "[grinsawl] #{t.name}: tier #{info[:tier] || '?'}, up to #{info[:cap]} per slot."
      info
    rescue StandardError => e
      respond "[grinsawl] couldn't read #{tome_label} tier: #{e.message}"
      nil
    end

    # You're a ghost: no capturing/foiling/analyzing/tome work until you're back.
    def self.dead?
      XMLData.indicator['IconDEAD'].to_s == 'y'
    rescue StandardError
      false
    end

    # On your feet? Anything else (sitting/kneeling/prone) usually means combat
    # has gone sideways, so we hold off capturing/foiling until you stand again.
    def self.upright?
      XMLData.indicator['IconSTANDING'].to_s == 'y'
    rescue StandardError
      true
    end

    # Live monsters in the room (ignores corpses/empties).
    def self.mob_count
      GameObj.targets.to_a.reject { |o| o.name.to_s.empty? || corpse?(o) }.size
    rescue StandardError
      0
    end

    # Room-claim awareness. Matches creaturewindow's CreatureWindow.claim_owned_room?
    # exactly (defined?(Lich::Claim) && Lich::Claim.mine?), so grinsawl and
    # creaturewindow agree on who owns the room. mine? is true only when you are
    # the sole non-grouped player present; another hunter makes it false.
    def self.claim_owned_room?
      (defined?(Lich::Claim) && Lich::Claim.mine?) ? true : false
    rescue StandardError
      false
    end

    # Should we hold for someone else's claim? Only when Claim is present AND the
    # room isn't ours. No Claim module (older Lich) or any Claim error -> not
    # contested, so grinsawl still works where claims aren't available.
    def self.room_contested?
      return false unless defined?(Lich::Claim)

      Match.room_contested?(available: true, mine: Lich::Claim.mine?)
    rescue StandardError
      false
    end

    # Why grinsawl should hold this tick (nil = clear to act). Edge-triggered
    # announce/clear keeps it from spamming while paused.
    def self.pause_reason
      return 'not standing (combat?)' if state[:pause_not_standing] && !upright?
      return 'another hunter is here (room claimed)' if state[:respect_claims] && room_contested?

      cap = state[:max_mobs].to_i
      n = mob_count
      return "too many monsters here (#{n} > #{cap})" if cap.positive? && n > cap

      nil
    end

    def self.note_paused(reason)
      return if state[:paused_reason] == reason

      state[:paused_reason] = reason
      respond "[grinsawl] holding off: #{reason}."
    end

    def self.note_resumed
      return unless state[:paused_reason]

      state[:paused_reason] = nil
      respond '[grinsawl] clear -- back to it.'
    end

    # Read both Collector vissi (verbs/cooldowns). A ghost can't ANALYZE, so this is skipped
    # while dead and re-run on revival (need_analyze). => true if it actually read them.
    def self.analyze_arcaria
      if dead?
        state[:need_analyze] = true
        return false
      end
      state[:aversaris] = analyze_arcarium('aversaris')
      state[:vangaris]  = analyze_arcarium('vangaris')
      %i[aversaris vangaris].each do |k|
        info = state[k]
        if info.nil?
          respond "[grinsawl] WARNING: couldn't read a Collector vissi in your #{k} arcarium."
        elsif info[:active] == false
          respond "[grinsawl] WARNING: your #{k} arcarium reads INERT -- prod it active before running."
        else
          respond "[grinsawl] #{k}: verb=#{info[:verb]} tier=#{info[:tier]} cooldown=#{info[:cooldown] || '?'}s"
        end
      end
      state[:need_analyze] = false
      true
    end

    def self.setup
      analyze_arcaria
      respond "[grinsawl] you are dead -- I'll read your arcaria when you're back among the living." if dead?
      # Open ready (status panel) if a card holder was set in a prior session -- even if
      # it hasn't re-resolved live yet -- and only fall into Setup for a first-time user.
      saved = !state[:card_sack_id].to_s.strip.empty? || !state[:card_sack_name].to_s.strip.empty?
      if configured? || saved
        state[:view] = :status
        state[:scan_sack_request] = true if configured? # first sack scan runs on the main loop
      else
        state[:view] = :setup
        respond '[grinsawl] no card-holder set -- opening Setup. Hold yours and click to assign it.'
      end
    end

    def self.cap_verb  = (state[:aversaris] && state[:aversaris][:verb]) || 'tap'
    def self.foil_verb = (state[:vangaris]  && state[:vangaris][:verb])  || 'tap'
    def self.cap_cd    = ((state[:aversaris] && state[:aversaris][:cooldown]) || 120).to_f
    def self.foil_cd   = ((state[:vangaris]  && state[:vangaris][:cooldown])  || 120).to_f

    # ---- cooldowns ----
    MILESTONES = [90, 60, 30, 10, 3].freeze # announce remaining time only at these marks

    def self.start_cd(which)
      cooldowns[which] = Time.now.to_f
      (state[:cd_marks] ||= {})[which] = [] # fresh cooldown, re-arm the milestone announcements
    end

    def self.ready?(which)
      cd = which == :aversaris ? cap_cd : foil_cd
      (Time.now.to_f - cooldowns[which].to_f) >= cd
    end

    def self.cd_left(which)
      cd = which == :aversaris ? cap_cd : foil_cd
      [0, (cd - (Time.now.to_f - cooldowns[which].to_f)).round].max
    end

    # m:ss with leading zeroes: 90->"1:30", 60->"1:00", 30->"0:30", 10->"0:10", 3->"0:03".
    def self.fmt_cd(s) = format('%d:%02d', s.to_i / 60, s.to_i % 60)

    # Quiet cooldown feedback: instead of echoing a per-tick countdown, announce a
    # capture/foil cooldown ONLY as it passes each milestone (1:30, 1:00, :30, :10, :3).
    def self.announce_cooldowns(kinds = %i[aversaris vangaris])
      { aversaris: 'Capture', vangaris: 'Foil' }.each do |which, label|
        next unless kinds.include?(which)
        next if ready?(which)

        marks = (state[:cd_marks] ||= {})[which] ||= []
        left = cd_left(which)
        m = MILESTONES.find { |ms| left <= ms && !marks.include?(ms) }
        next unless m

        marks << m
        respond "[grinsawl] #{label} ready in #{fmt_cd(m)}"
      end
    end

    # Pause the configured scripts (e.g. energywings) around an activation so they
    # can't act mid-capture, then ALWAYS unpause -- on success, failure, or error.
    def self.with_pause
      paused = state[:pause_list].select { |n| (Script.running?(n) rescue false) }
      paused.each { |n| pause_script(n) rescue nil }
      begin
        yield
      ensure
        paused.each { |n| unpause_script(n) rescue nil }
      end
    end

    # ---- inventory / stock ----
    # LIVE: LOOK at each grinsawl in the working sack to seed the ledger from cards
    # you already own (creature + foil status). Slow; runs at setup and on demand.
    def self.scan_sack
      ensure_sack_loaded
      # Loose cards live in the sack OR in a hand (a freshly captured or retrieved
      # card sits in hand); track both so a hand card isn't pruned away.
      grins = (sack_contents + held).select { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }.uniq(&:id)
      here_ids = grins.map { |o| o.id.to_s }
      ledger.keys.each { |id| ledger.delete(id) unless here_ids.include?(id) } # drop cards no longer loose
      grins.each do |o|
        next if ledger.key?(o.id.to_s)

        info = look_card(o.id)
        ledger[o.id.to_s] = info if info && info[:creature]
      end
      # a card now in the sack is NOT in the tome -- drop any stale tome copy
      state[:tome_cards] = tome_cards.reject { |c| here_ids.include?(c[:id].to_s) }
    end

    def self.look_card(id)
      lines = Lich::Util.issue_command(
        "look at ##{id}",
        /grinsawl|could not find|What were you/i, /<prompt/,
        include_end: false, timeout: 5, usexml: true, quiet: true, use_fput: false
      )
      Parse.card(strip(lines))
    end

    # unfoiled cards matching the goal (partial name) still in sack or hand (LOOSE).
    def self.unfoiled_goal_ids
      return [] unless goal

      here = (sack_contents + held).map { |o| o.id.to_s }
      ledger.select do |id, info|
        here.include?(id) && info[:foil].nil? && Match.goal_match?(goal[:creature], info[:creature])
      end.keys
    end

    # Unfoiled goal cards FILED IN THE TOME (the foiler can pull one out if no loose copy).
    def self.tome_unfoiled_goal
      return [] unless goal

      tome_cards.select { |c| c[:foil].nil? && Match.goal_match?(goal[:creature], c[:creature]) }
    end

    # Creatures we can foil toward the goal -- loose OR filed -- so the planner picks foil
    # even when the only unfoiled copy lives in the tome.
    def self.unfoiled_goal_creatures
      (unfoiled_goal_ids.map { |id| ledger[id][:creature] } +
       tome_unfoiled_goal.map { |c| c[:creature] }).compact.uniq
    end

    # Backlog = unfoiled goal cards anywhere (loose + filed, qty-expanded), so we do not
    # over-capture when unfoiled copies are already filed.
    def self.stock = unfoiled_goal_ids.size + tome_unfoiled_goal.sum { |c| [c[:qty].to_i, 1].max }

    # ---- tome snapshot (persisted, trusted, rescan-on-demand) ----
    def self.tome_cards = state[:tome_cards] || []

    def self.save_tome_cache
      CharSettings['tome_cards']      = state[:tome_cards]
      CharSettings['tome_scanned_at'] = state[:tome_scanned_at]
    end

    # Persist config to CharSettings. MUST run on the script's main thread (Script.current
    # is nil in the UpstreamHook/client thread, which silently aborts the save), so the
    # hook only flags :config_dirty and the main loop calls this.
    def self.persist_config
      CharSettings['card_sack_id']   = state[:card_sack_id]
      CharSettings['card_sack_name'] = state[:card_sack_name]
      CharSettings['tome_id']        = state[:tome_id]
      CharSettings['tome_name']      = state[:tome_name]
      CharSettings['pause_list']     = state[:pause_list]
      CharSettings['default_min']    = state[:default_min].to_s
      CharSettings['goal']           = self.goal
      CharSettings['tome_cap']       = state[:tome_cap]
      CharSettings['disable_spell']   = state[:disable_spell].to_s
      CharSettings['disable_enabled'] = state[:disable_enabled] ? true : false
      CharSettings['max_mobs']        = state[:max_mobs].to_i
      CharSettings['respect_claims']  = state[:respect_claims] ? true : false
      CharSettings['fold_collection'] = state[:fold_collection] ? true : false
      CharSettings['fold_retrieve']   = state[:fold_retrieve] ? true : false
      CharSettings['pause_not_standing'] = state[:pause_not_standing] ? true : false
      state[:config_dirty] = false
    rescue StandardError => e
      respond "[grinsawl] config save error: #{e.message}"
    end

    # Merged {creature, foil} entries across the loose sack ledger AND the cached
    # tome (qty-expanded) -- the whole collection, for Tracking and target counts.
    # Deduped (by card id) merge of the sack ledger and the tome cache; see
    # Summary.dedup_inventory.
    def self.inventory_entries
      Summary.dedup_inventory(ledger, tome_cards)
    end

    def self.tome_io(cmd, start_rx, quiet: true)
      Lich::Util.issue_command(cmd, start_rx, /<prompt/, include_end: false, timeout: 8, usexml: true, quiet: quiet, use_fput: false)
    rescue StandardError => e
      respond "[grinsawl] tome I/O error on '#{cmd}': #{e.message}"
      []
    end

    # Walk every leaf once -> a live model of the whole tome. INSPECT reads the current
    # leaf (grid + "Nth open leaf"); flip advances; stop when a leaf repeats (wrap) or is
    # unreadable. Flavor-agnostic: never parses the customizable open/close/name prose.
    # => { model: [{leaf:, slot:, card: nil|slot-hash}], cards: [occupied + :leaf], leaves: [n] }
    def self.walk_tome(t)
      tome_io("open ##{t.id}", /ripple|cover|latch|flatten|You open|already open|leaf|can't|don't|What were you|seem to|no way/i)
      model = []
      cards = []
      leaves = []
      seen = {}
      14.times do
        insp = tome_io("inspect ##{t.id}", /open leaf|thumb your fingers|\bleaf\b|empty slot|grinsawl|study/i)
        leafno = strip(insp).map { |l| Grinsawl::Tome.flip_leaf(l) }.compact.first
        break if leafno.nil? || seen[leafno] # nil (unreadable) or wrapped back to a read leaf

        seen[leafno] = true
        state[:cur_leaf] = leafno
        leaves << leafno
        Grinsawl::Tome.leaf(insp)[:slots].each_with_index do |sl, i|
          model << { leaf: leafno, slot: i + 1, card: sl }
          cards << sl.merge(leaf: leafno) if sl
        end
        tome_io("flip ##{t.id}", /arrive at the|flip through|\bleaf\b|reached the end|back to the first|can't|What were you/i)
        state[:cur_leaf] = nil # we just flipped; re-establish on the next inspect
      end
      # leave the tome open (closing is unnecessary)
      { model: model, cards: cards, leaves: leaves }
    end

    # Scan every leaf -> persisted snapshot (occupied slots only).
    # Full walk -> refresh the cache (cards + leaf count + scanned-at), prune the loose
    # ledger, persist. Shared by the scan command, the organizer's first open, and Rescan.
    def self.scan_tome_into_cache(t)
      walk = walk_tome(t)
      state[:tome_cards] = walk[:cards]
      state[:tome_leaves] = Array(walk[:leaves]).map(&:to_i).max
      state[:tome_scanned_at] = Time.now.to_i
      reconcile_loose_ledger
      save_tome_cache
      walk
    end

    def self.scan_tome
      t = tome
      unless t
        respond "[grinsawl] no #{tome_label} assigned -- assign it in Setup."
        return false
      end
      respond "[grinsawl] scanning #{t.name}..."
      walk = scan_tome_into_cache(t)
      respond "[grinsawl] #{t.name} scan complete: #{walk[:cards].size} card(s) across #{walk[:leaves].size} leaf/leaves."
      true
    end

    # Read which leaf the tome is open to (one inspect), caching it in state[:cur_leaf].
    def self.current_leaf(t)
      insp = tome_io("inspect ##{t.id}", /open leaf|thumb your fingers|\bleaf\b|empty slot|grinsawl|study/i)
      state[:cur_leaf] = strip(insp).map { |l| Grinsawl::Tome.flip_leaf(l) }.compact.first
    end

    # Turn the tome to a specific leaf. Reads the leaf straight from each FLIP response
    # (no inspect per step) and tracks state[:cur_leaf], so it costs ~one flip per leaf
    # traversed instead of an inspect+flip, and repeated calls in one op don't re-scan.
    # => true once on that leaf, false if unreachable.
    def self.goto_leaf(t, target)
      cur = state[:cur_leaf] || current_leaf(t)
      return true if cur == target

      18.times do
        fl  = tome_io("flip ##{t.id}", /arrive at the|land on the|flip back|reached the end|flip through|\bleaf\b|can't|What were you/i)
        cur = strip(fl).map { |l| Grinsawl::Tome.flip_leaf(l) }.compact.first
        cur ||= current_leaf(t) # flip text unreadable -> fall back to an inspect
        state[:cur_leaf] = cur
        return true if cur == target
      end
      false
    end

    # A store/stack took if the tome confirms it OR the card has left our hand (stacking
    # onto a matching card may print different flavor, but the held card is consumed
    # either way). Brief poll because the hand state updates asynchronously.
    def self.store_took?(res, id)
      return true if strip(res).any? { |l| Grinsawl::Tome.stored?(l) }

      20.times do
        return true unless held.any? { |o| o.id.to_s == id.to_s }

        sleep 0.1
      end
      false
    end

    # File grinsawl cards from the card sack INTO the tome. which = :foiled (default,
    # finished cards) or :all. Cards with an identical depicted name and the same foil
    # STACK onto an existing slot that has room; otherwise an empty slot is used. One
    # leaf walk builds the slot model (also refreshing the cache); then each card is
    # placed and we turn to its leaf before tapping. Runs on the main loop (queued),
    # wrapped in with_pause.
    def self.store_cards(which = :foiled)
      t = tome
      return respond("[grinsawl] no #{tome_label} assigned -- assign it in Setup.") unless t

      ensure_sack_loaded
      # Source from the ACTUAL grinsawls in the sack (not just the ledger); read foil
      # from the ledger, else LOOK at the card.
      grins = sack_contents.select { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }
      candidates = grins.map do |o|
        info = ledger[o.id.to_s] || look_card(o.id) || {}
        ledger[o.id.to_s] = info if info[:creature]
        { id: o.id.to_s, creature: info[:creature], foil: info[:foil] }
      end
      candidates.select! { |c| which == :all || !c[:foil].nil? }
      if candidates.empty?
        respond "[grinsawl] nothing to store (#{which}) -- #{grins.size} grinsawl(s) in your #{sack_label}."
        return
      end

      respond "[grinsawl] storing #{candidates.size} #{which} card(s) into #{t.name} (stacking matching cards)..."
      stored = 0
      stacked = 0
      aborted = false
      # Store needs BOTH hands (ledger + card), so with_tome_hands sets aside whatever the
      # user is holding, brings the tome to hand for the block, then puts the tome away and
      # restores their gear.
      with_pause do
        with_tome_hands(t) do |ok|
          unless ok # filing needs the ledger held, not just referenced by id
            aborted = true
            next
          end
          walk = walk_tome(t)                       # one pass: authoritative slot model + fresh cache
          model = walk[:model]
          state[:tome_cards] = walk[:cards]
          state[:tome_scanned_at] = Time.now.to_i
          taken = [] # [leaf, slot] filled this batch -- never reuse an empty slot for a different card
          candidates.each do |c|
            place = Summary.place_card(model, c[:creature], c[:foil], cap: state[:tome_cap], taken: taken)
            unless place
              respond "[grinsawl] #{t.name} is full -- no slot for #{c[:creature]}."
              break
            end
            unless goto_leaf(t, place[:leaf])
              respond "[grinsawl] couldn't turn to leaf #{place[:leaf]}; stopping."
              break
            end
            unless get_from_sack(c[:id])
              respond "[grinsawl] couldn't pull #{c[:creature]} from your #{sack_label}; skipping."
              next
            end
            res = tome_io("tap ##{t.id} at #{place[:slot]}",
                          /grafted likeness remains|join|combine|merg|alongside|existing|stack|already|can't|full|no room|doesn't match|What were you/i)
            if store_took?(res, c[:id])
              apply_store(model, place, c)
              taken << [place[:leaf], place[:slot]] if place[:mode] == :empty
              ledger.delete(c[:id])
              stored += 1
              stacked += 1 if place[:mode] == :stack
            else
              respond "[grinsawl] store of #{c[:creature]} didn't take (#{strip(res).reject(&:empty?).first}); stopping."
              break
            end
          end
        end
      end
      return if aborted

      save_tome_cache
      tail = stacked.positive? ? " (#{stacked} stacked onto matching cards)" : ''
      respond "[grinsawl] stored #{stored} card(s) into your #{t.name}#{tail}."
    end

    # Record a successful store in both the live model (so the next card in the batch
    # sees the update) and the persisted cache: bump qty on a stack, else add the slot.
    def self.apply_store(model, place, card)
      ment = model.find { |e| e[:leaf] == place[:leaf] && e[:slot] == place[:slot] }
      tent = (state[:tome_cards] ||= []).find { |tc| tc[:leaf] == place[:leaf] && tc[:slot] == place[:slot] }
      if place[:mode] == :stack
        ment[:card][:qty] = ment[:card][:qty].to_i + 1 if ment && ment[:card]
        tent[:qty] = tent[:qty].to_i + 1 if tent
      else
        entry = { slot: place[:slot], leaf: place[:leaf], id: card[:id], creature: card[:creature], foil: card[:foil], qty: 1 }
        ment[:card] = entry if ment
        state[:tome_cards].reject! { |tc| tc[:id].to_s == card[:id].to_s } # no duplicate-id entries
        state[:tome_cards] << entry
      end
    end

    # ---- retrieve (pull a filed card back to hand) ----
    # Drop one copy of a retrieved card from the cached snapshot (decrement a stacked
    # slot, else remove the entry). Keyed on the STABLE leaf+slot, not the card's exist
    # id (tome card ids are regenerated on every render -- see retrieve_one).
    def self.remove_tome_card(card)
      arr = state[:tome_cards] || []
      idx = arr.index { |c| c[:leaf] == card[:leaf] && c[:slot] == card[:slot] } ||
            arr.index { |c| c[:id].to_s == card[:id].to_s }
      return unless idx

      if arr[idx][:qty].to_i > 1
        arr[idx] = arr[idx].merge(qty: arr[idx][:qty].to_i - 1)
      else
        arr.delete_at(idx)
      end
    end

    # Parse "[bronze|silver|gold|card] <creature>" and pull the matching filed card to
    # hand. Runs on the main loop (queued), wrapped in with_pause. The card is left in
    # hand so you can use, trade, or sell it; a later store/scan re-files or re-counts it.
    def self.run_retrieve(args)
      t = tome
      return respond("[grinsawl] no #{tome_label} assigned -- assign it in Setup.") unless t
      return respond("[grinsawl] no #{tome_label} scan yet -- scan it (Setup) so I know what's filed.") if tome_cards.empty?

      parts = args.to_s.split
      first = parts[0].to_s.downcase
      tier = Grinsawl::Tier.normalize(first)
      unfoiled = %w[card white unfoiled none plain].include?(first)
      creature = ((tier || unfoiled) ? parts[1..] : parts).to_a.join(' ').strip.downcase
      if creature.empty?
        return respond('[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl retrieve [bronze|silver|gold|card] <creature>')
      end

      card = Summary.pick_card(tome_cards, creature, tier: tier, unfoiled: unfoiled)
      unless card
        desc = tier ? tier.to_s : (unfoiled ? 'unfoiled' : 'matching')
        return respond("[grinsawl] no #{desc} #{creature} card filed in your #{t.name}.")
      end
      retrieve_one(t, card)
    end

    # A tome card's exist id is EPHEMERAL -- the ledger regenerates it on every leaf
    # render, so the id captured at scan time is stale (a stale `get #<id>#` gives
    # "Get what?"). Only the leaf+slot is stable. So turn to the card's leaf, INSPECT to
    # read the CURRENT id for that slot, and get it immediately (no render in between).
    def self.retrieve_one(t, card)
      state[:cur_leaf] = nil # standalone op: verify the leaf with one inspect, don't trust a stale cache
      with_pause do
        with_tome_hands(t) do |ok| # grabs the tome (setting your held gear aside) -- getting a card needs it held
          unless ok
            respond "[grinsawl] retrieve skipped: couldn't get your #{t.name} in hand."
            next
          end
          unless card[:leaf] && goto_leaf(t, card[:leaf])
            respond "[grinsawl] couldn't turn to leaf #{card[:leaf]} for #{card[:creature]} -- rescan your #{t.name}."
            next
          end
          insp = tome_io("inspect ##{t.id}", /open leaf|thumb your fingers|\bleaf\b|empty slot|grinsawl|study/i)
          fresh = (Grinsawl::Tome.leaf(insp)[:slots] || [])[card[:slot].to_i - 1]
          unless fresh && fresh[:id]
            respond "[grinsawl] slot #{card[:slot]} on leaf #{card[:leaf]} is empty now -- rescan your #{t.name}."
            next
          end
          if card[:creature] && fresh[:creature] && !Match.identical?(card[:creature], fresh[:creature])
            respond "[grinsawl] leaf #{card[:leaf]} slot #{card[:slot]} now holds #{fresh[:creature]}, not #{card[:creature]} -- rescan your #{t.name}."
            next
          end
          # fresh[:id] carries the anchor's trailing '#', so `get #<id>` is `get #424352439#`.
          res = tome_io("get ##{fresh[:id]}",
                        /separates cleanly|don't (?:see|have)|can't|isn't (?:here|in)|no .*grinsawl|not your|What were you|Get what/i)
          got = strip(res).map { |l| Grinsawl::Tome.retrieved?(l) }.compact.first
          if got
            remove_tome_card(card)
            g = nil
            15.times { g = held_grinsawl; break if g; sleep 0.1 } # GameObj hand updates async
            ledger[(g ? g.id.to_s : "ret_#{card[:leaf]}_#{card[:slot]}")] = { creature: got[:creature], foil: got[:foil] }
            save_tome_cache
            respond "[grinsawl] retrieved a #{got[:foil] || 'unfoiled'} #{got[:creature]} card to your hand."
          else
            respond "[grinsawl] retrieve didn't take (#{strip(res).reject(&:empty?).first}); rescan if your #{t.name} changed."
          end
        end
      end
    end

    # Drop ONE loose ledger card matching (creature, foil) -- used when we see a card
    # thrown away, so the collection count updates without a rescan. Returns true if one
    # was removed.
    def self.remove_loose(creature, foil)
      hit = ledger.find { |_id, info| info && Match.identical?(info[:creature], creature) && info[:foil] == foil }
      hit ? (ledger.delete(hit.first); true) : false
    end

    # `grinsawl clean`: pull bronze/silver cards to your hand ONE at a time so you can THROW
    # them to discard them. Command-only. Prefers a loose copy (just hands it over); falls
    # back to one filed in the tome. Re-run after each throw for the next.
    def self.run_clean
      # already holding a bronze/silver? wait for the player to throw it before pulling more.
      holding = held.find do |o|
        next false unless o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i

        i = ledger[o.id.to_s] || look_card(o.id) || {}
        %i[bronze silver].include?(i[:foil])
      end
      return respond('[grinsawl] THROW the card in your hand first, then ;grinsawl clean for the next.') if holding

      ensure_sack_loaded

      # Scan the CARD PACK for loose bronze/silver -- LOOK at each card rather than
      # trusting the ledger, since a relogin regenerates card ids and leaves the ledger
      # stale (which used to make clean wrongly report "nothing to clean").
      loose_bs = []
      sack_contents.select { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }.each do |o|
        info = ledger[o.id.to_s] || look_card(o.id) || {}
        ledger[o.id.to_s] = info if info[:creature]
        loose_bs << { id: o.id.to_s, creature: info[:creature], foil: info[:foil] } if %i[bronze silver].include?(info[:foil])
      end

      t = tome
      tome_bs = Array(tome_cards).select { |c| %i[bronze silver].include?(c[:foil]) }
      remaining = loose_bs.size + tome_bs.sum { |c| [c[:qty].to_i, 1].max }
      return respond('[grinsawl] no bronze or silver cards to clean (checked your pack and tome).') if remaining.zero?

      # Prefer a loose one already in the pack (no tome handling needed).
      if (loose = loose_bs.first)
        return respond('[grinsawl] free a hand first (or throw what you are holding), then ;grinsawl clean.') unless a_hand_free?

        if get_from_sack(loose[:id])
          respond "[grinsawl] #{loose[:foil]} #{cap(loose[:creature])} in your hand -- THROW it to discard, then ;grinsawl clean for the next (~#{remaining - 1} left)."
        else
          respond "[grinsawl] couldn't pull the #{loose[:foil]} #{loose[:creature]} from your #{sack_label}."
        end
        return
      end

      # else pull one filed in the tome (retrieve_one handles hands/the tome)
      if (tcard = tome_bs.first)
        retrieve_one(t, tcard)
        respond "[grinsawl] THROW it to discard, then ;grinsawl clean for the next (~#{remaining - 1} left)."
      else
        respond '[grinsawl] no loose bronze/silver to clean -- the rest may be filed (scan your tome first).'
      end
    end

    # ---- present creatures ----
    # A dead creature still lingers as a target but capturing/foiling it just burns the
    # cooldown, so it must never be chosen or acted on. Lich marks the kill in .status.
    def self.corpse?(obj)
      return false unless obj

      (obj.status.to_s =~ /dead/i) || (obj.name.to_s =~ /\bcorpse\b/i) ? true : false
    rescue StandardError
      false
    end

    # Hostile mobs only -- GameObj.targets is the game's real target list (the same
    # source creaturewindow uses), so it already excludes shopkeepers, other
    # players' animated weapons/summons (^animated), severed limbs, and the dead.
    # We do NOT add GameObj.npcs, which would drag those non-hostiles back in.
    def self.present_objs
      GameObj.targets.to_a.compact.uniq(&:id)
        .select { |o| !o.name.to_s.empty? && !corpse?(o) && Match.wanted?(o.name, state[:want], state[:avoid]) }
    end

    # ---- executors ----
    # Activation terminal patterns. They include the LINK-BREAK ("the tether becomes
    # impossible...the radiance fades into nothingness" / "leaving your grinsawl unharmed")
    # and NO-TARGET phrasings so an interrupted attempt ends in ~1s instead of waiting the
    # full timeout. NO_FIRE means the activation never went off -- do NOT spend a cooldown.
    WARN_SECS = 2 # heads-up before grinsawl issues a capture/foil, so you can weave your own hunting
    # The activation never actually went off (no target, can't act, or bounced off
    # roundtime) -- so do NOT spend a cooldown; the next tick can simply retry. (A nil
    # result, i.e. await_link saw no success/break at all, is handled the same way.)
    NO_FIRE_RX = /need to specify a target|activate your Collector vissi|you can't|cannot|no longer (?:here|alive)|isn't here|not a valid|What were you|wait \d+ sec|still (?:recovering|stunned)|not (?:yet )?recovered/i
    CAPTURE_END_RX = /solidifies into a radiant white grinsawl bearing the image of|failed card capture|the (?:magical )?link (?:fades|expires)|tether (?:becomes impossible|untwines)|too much distance between you|radiance fades into nothingness|need to specify a target|Collector vissi|you can't|cannot|no longer here|isn't here|What were you/i
    FOIL_END_RX = /your card now bears a luxuriant (?:bronze|silver|gold) foil|identical creature|tether (?:becomes impossible|untwines)|too much distance between you|leaving your grinsawl unharmed|need to specify a target|Collector vissi|you can't|cannot|no longer here|isn't here|What were you/i

    # A RESISTED capture/foil turns into a multi-round "battle of wills" that can
    # run well past one roundtime. These lines mean the contest is STILL GOING --
    # they are NOT terminal. While we see them we keep waiting (and keep the
    # pause-list scripts paused, since any action on your part breaks the link).
    CONTEST_RX = /resists the anchor|battle of wills|you strain against/i
    LINK_IDLE_WAIT = 30  # seconds with no progress/terminal line before we give up
    LINK_HARD_CAP  = 180 # absolute ceiling so a stuck contest can never hang forever

    # Send an activation, then wait for it to TRULY resolve. Returns the terminal
    # line (success / fail / no-fire) or nil if it stalled. Each battle-of-wills
    # progress line refreshes the patience window, so a long resisted contest is
    # not cut short the way a flat timeout would (and we never report a still-live
    # capture as failed).
    def self.await_link(cmd, end_rx)
      # Wait out any roundtime first so the activation doesn't just bounce ("Wait 3
      # sec.") -- hard RT from your swings, and the cast RT from the disabling spell.
      waitrt? rescue nil
      waitcastrt? rescue nil
      fput cmd
      hard = Time.now + LINK_HARD_CAP
      loop do
        remaining = hard - Time.now
        return nil if remaining <= 0

        line = matchtimeout([[LINK_IDLE_WAIT, remaining].min, 0.5].max,
                            end_rx.source, NO_FIRE_RX.source, CONTEST_RX.source)
        return line if line.is_a?(String) && (line =~ end_rx || line =~ NO_FIRE_RX)
        return nil unless line.is_a?(String) && line =~ CONTEST_RX
        # contest still going -- loop; the next matchtimeout refreshes the window
      end
    end

    # Capture/foil break if the creature flees, so cast the user's configured disabling spell
    # (e.g. 709) FIRST to keep it in the room. No-op if disabled/unset. A BARE NUMBER is cast
    # with INCANT (`incant 709`); anything else is sent verbatim, with `{target}` replaced by
    # the creature's id so single-target commands can aim (e.g. `cast 901 at {target}`).
    def self.disable_target(obj)
      return unless state[:disable_enabled]

      spell = state[:disable_spell].to_s.strip
      return if spell.empty? || obj.nil? || corpse?(obj)

      cmd = spell =~ /\A\d+\z/ ? "incant #{spell}" : spell.gsub('{target}', "##{obj.id}")
      with_pause do
        dothistimeout(cmd,
                      8, /Cast Roundtime|you gesture|you recite|Warding (?:failed|is)|fully resists|takes? root|is (?:rooted|held|ensnared|entangled)|cannot move|lack (?:the|sufficient)|don't have (?:enough|the)|insufficient|isn't here|no longer (?:here|alive)|not a valid|incant what|cast at what|What were you/i)
      end
    end

    def self.do_capture(obj)
      return if dead?
      return respond('[grinsawl] capture skipped: that target is a corpse.') if corpse?(obj)

      disable_target(obj) # root it first so it can't flee and break the link
      unless free_hand! # stows a loose grinsawl, never your equipped/held gear
        respond '[grinsawl] capture skipped: no free hand (keeping your held items).'
        return
      end
      result = with_pause do
        await_link("#{cap_verb} my aversaris arcarium at ##{obj.id}", CAPTURE_END_RX)
      end
      if result.nil? || result.to_s =~ NO_FIRE_RX
        respond '[grinsawl] capture did not go off (roundtime or no target); will retry.'
        return # activation never fired -- do not spend the cooldown, so the next tick retries
      end
      start_cd(:aversaris)
      res = Parse.capture_result(result)
      if res.is_a?(Hash)
        g = held_grinsawl
        if g
          ledger[g.id.to_s] = { creature: res[:creature], foil: nil }
          stow_to_sack(g.id)
        end
        respond "[grinsawl] captured #{res[:creature]} (stock now #{stock})"
      else
        respond "[grinsawl] capture of #{Match.normalize(obj.name)} did not take (link broke or resisted)."
      end
    end

    # Put an unfoiled card of `cname` into hand to foil: prefer a LOOSE copy (sack/hand),
    # else pull one out of the TOME. Returns the held card's id, or nil if none anywhere.
    def self.bring_unfoiled_to_hand(cname)
      loose = unfoiled_goal_ids.find { |cid| Match.identical?(ledger[cid][:creature], cname) }
      if loose
        return loose if held.any? { |o| o.id.to_s == loose } # already in hand

        free_hand! # free a hand (stows a loose grinsawl, never your gear) to hold the card
        return loose if get_from_sack(loose)
      end
      # fall back to an unfoiled copy filed in the tome (retrieve_one frees a hand itself)
      t = tome
      tcard = t && tome_unfoiled_goal.find { |c| Match.identical?(c[:creature], cname) }
      if tcard && retrieve_one(t, tcard)
        g = held_grinsawl
        return g.id.to_s if g
      end
      nil
    end

    def self.do_foil(obj)
      return if dead?
      return respond('[grinsawl] foil skipped: that target is a corpse.') if corpse?(obj)

      disable_target(obj) # root it first so it can't flee and break the link
      cname = Match.normalize(obj.name)
      id = bring_unfoiled_to_hand(cname)
      unless id
        respond "[grinsawl] no unfoiled #{cname} card available to foil (loose or filed)."
        return
      end
      result = with_pause do
        await_link("#{foil_verb} my vangaris arcarium at ##{obj.id}", FOIL_END_RX)
      end
      if result.nil? || result.to_s =~ NO_FIRE_RX
        respond '[grinsawl] foil did not go off (roundtime or no target); will retry.'
        return # activation never fired -- do not spend the cooldown, so the next tick retries
      end
      start_cd(:vangaris)
      res = Parse.foil_result(result)
      if res.is_a?(Hash)
        tier = res[:tier]
        ledger[id] = { creature: cname, foil: tier }
        if Grinsawl::Tier.meets?(tier, goal[:min])
          respond ">>>> GRINSAWL GOAL: #{tier.to_s.upcase} #{cname} acquired! <<<<"
          state[:active] = false
        else
          state[:byproducts] += 1
          respond "[grinsawl] foiled #{cname} -> #{tier} (byproduct; goal is #{goal[:min]}+)"
        end
        g = held_grinsawl
        stow_to_sack(g.id) if g
      elsif res == :mismatch
        respond '[grinsawl] foil rejected: that was not an identical creature.'
      elsif res == :broke
        respond '[grinsawl] foil link broke (target moved); cooldown spent.'
      else
        respond "[grinsawl] foil inconclusive."
      end
    end

    # ---- command interface ----
    def self.set_goal(args)
      parts = args.to_s.split
      min = Grinsawl::Tier.normalize(parts[0])
      creature = parts[1..].to_a.join(' ').strip.downcase
      if min.nil? || creature.empty?
        respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl <bronze|silver|gold> <creature>'
        return false
      end
      self.goal = { creature: creature, min: min }
      state[:default_min] = min
      state[:config_dirty] = true
      state[:byproducts] = 0
      state[:active] = configured?
      respond(configured? ? "[grinsawl] goal: a #{min}+ #{creature} card. Working the current room." \
                          : "[grinsawl] goal: a #{min}+ #{creature} card. Set a card sack (Setup) to start.")
      true
    end

    def self.handle_command(sub)
      cmd, rest = sub.to_s.strip.split(/\s+/, 2)
      case cmd.to_s.downcase
      when '', 'status' then print_status
      when 'view'  then state[:view] = (rest.to_s.strip.downcase == 'setup' ? :setup : :status)
      when 'goal'  then set_goal(rest)
      when 'target'
        cre = rest.to_s.strip.downcase
        if cre.empty?
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl target <creature>'
        else
          self.goal ||= { creature: cre, min: state[:default_min] }
          goal[:creature] = cre
          goal[:min] ||= state[:default_min]
          state[:active] = true if configured?
          state[:config_dirty] = true # remember the goal across sessions
          respond "[grinsawl] target: #{goal[:min]} #{cre}#{configured? ? '' : ' (set a card sack in Setup to start)'}"
        end
      when 'min'
        m = Grinsawl::Tier.normalize(rest)
        if m
          state[:default_min] = m
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          goal[:min] = m if goal
          respond(m == :cap ? '[grinsawl] capture only (no foiling).' : "[grinsawl] foil goal -> #{m}")
        else
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl min <cap|bronze|silver|gold>'
        end
      when 'tometier', 'tier'
        if rest.to_s.strip.empty?
          state[:detect_tier_request] = true # game I/O -> run on the main loop
          respond '[grinsawl] reading tome tier...'
        else
          cap = { '1' => 1, '2' => 5, '3' => 20 }[rest.to_s.strip]
          if cap
            state[:tome_cap] = cap
            state[:config_dirty] = true
            respond "[grinsawl] tome tier #{rest.strip}: up to #{cap} per slot."
          else
            respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl tometier (auto-detect) or <1|2|3> (1/5/20), or grinsawl tomecap <n>'
          end
        end
      when 'tomecap'
        n = rest.to_s.strip.to_i
        if n.positive?
          state[:tome_cap] = n
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond "[grinsawl] stack cap -> #{n} per slot."
        else
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl tomecap <n>'
        end
      when 'maxmobs', 'maxmob', 'mobs'
        arg = rest.to_s.strip.downcase
        if arg.empty?
          m = state[:max_mobs].to_i
          respond "[grinsawl] max monsters: #{m.positive? ? "pause when more than #{m} in the room" : 'off'}. Set with grinsawl maxmobs <n> (0 = off)."
        elsif arg =~ /\A\d+\z/ || %w[off none].include?(arg)
          state[:max_mobs] = arg =~ /\A\d+\z/ ? arg.to_i : 0
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond state[:max_mobs].positive? ? "[grinsawl] will pause when more than #{state[:max_mobs]} monster(s) are in the room." : '[grinsawl] max-monsters pause OFF.'
        else
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl maxmobs <n>  (0 or off to disable)'
        end
      when 'claims', 'claim'
        case rest.to_s.strip.downcase
        when ''
          avail = defined?(Lich::Claim) ? '' : ' (no Claim module in this Lich -- has no effect here)'
          respond "[grinsawl] respect other hunters' room claims: #{state[:respect_claims] ? 'ON' : 'OFF'}#{avail}. Toggle with grinsawl claims on|off."
        when 'on', 'yes', 'true'
          state[:respect_claims] = true
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond '[grinsawl] respecting claims ON -- will hold when another hunter is in the room.'
        when 'off', 'no', 'false'
          state[:respect_claims] = false
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond '[grinsawl] respecting claims OFF.'
        else
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl claims on|off'
        end
      when 'fold', 'collapse', 'expand'
        sec = rest.to_s.strip.downcase
        key = sec.start_with?('coll') ? :fold_collection : sec.start_with?('ret') ? :fold_retrieve : nil
        if key
          state[key] = case cmd.downcase
                       when 'collapse' then true
                       when 'expand'   then false
                       else !state[key] # 'fold' toggles (what the [-]/[+] buttons send)
                       end
          state[:config_dirty] = true
        else
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl fold collection|retrieve'
        end
      when 'standpause'
        state[:pause_not_standing] = case rest.to_s.strip.downcase
                                     when 'on'  then true
                                     when 'off' then false
                                     else !state[:pause_not_standing] # button toggles
                                     end
        state[:config_dirty] = true
        respond "[grinsawl] auto-pause when not standing: #{state[:pause_not_standing] ? 'ON' : 'OFF'}."
      when 'spell', 'disable'
        raw = rest.to_s.strip
        case raw.downcase
        when ''
          have = state[:disable_spell].to_s.empty? ? '(unset)' : state[:disable_spell]
          respond "[grinsawl] disabling spell: #{have}, currently #{state[:disable_enabled] ? 'ON' : 'OFF'}. Set with grinsawl spell <number>; toggle with grinsawl spell on|off."
        when 'on'
          if state[:disable_spell].to_s.empty?
            respond '[grinsawl] set a spell first: grinsawl spell <number>'
          else
            state[:disable_enabled] = true
            state[:config_dirty] = true
            respond "[grinsawl] disabling spell ON (cast #{state[:disable_spell]} at the target before capture/foil)."
          end
        when 'off', 'none', 'clear', '0', 'stop'
          state[:disable_enabled] = false
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond '[grinsawl] disabling spell OFF (will not cast).'
        else
          state[:disable_spell] = raw # preserve case in case it's a command, not just a number
          state[:disable_enabled] = true
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond "[grinsawl] disabling spell -> #{raw} (ON; cast at the target before capture/foil). grinsawl spell off to disable."
        end
      when 'go', 'start', 'resume'
        if !configured? then respond '[grinsawl] set a card container first (grinsawl view setup).'
        elsif goal.nil?  then respond '[grinsawl] pick a target first.'
        else state[:active] = true; respond "[grinsawl] Watching for #{cap(goal[:creature])}..." end
      when 'setsack', 'settome'
        role = cmd.downcase == 'setsack' ? 'card_sack' : 'tome'
        label = role == 'card_sack' ? 'card container' : 'card book'
        arg = rest.to_s.strip
        if arg =~ /\A(?:none|clear|remove|off|unset)\z/i
          state["#{role}_id".to_sym] = nil
          state["#{role}_name".to_sym] = nil
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond "[grinsawl] #{label} cleared."
          return
        end
        o = (arg.empty? || arg =~ /\A(?:hand|held)\z/i) ? held_item : find_inv(arg)
        if o
          state["#{role}_id".to_sym]   = o.id.to_s
          state["#{role}_name".to_sym] = o.name.to_s
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          hint = role == 'card_sack' ? ' (stow it so I can reach its contents)' : ''
          respond "[grinsawl] #{label} set to #{o.name}#{hint} (remembered by name)"
          state[:scan_sack_request] = true if role == 'card_sack' # scan on the main thread
        else
          respond '[grinsawl] hold the item in a hand first, then click again.'
        end
      when 'pause', 'unpause', 'pausetoggle'
        n = rest.to_s.strip
        if n.empty?
          respond "[grinsawl] pause-list: #{state[:pause_list].empty? ? '(none)' : state[:pause_list].join(', ')}"
        else
          present = state[:pause_list].include?(n)
          add = cmd.downcase == 'unpause' ? false : (cmd.downcase == 'pause' ? true : !present)
          add ? (state[:pause_list] << n unless present) : state[:pause_list].delete(n)
          state[:config_dirty] = true
          respond "[grinsawl] pause-list: #{state[:pause_list].empty? ? '(none)' : state[:pause_list].join(', ')}"
        end
      when 'want'  then state[:want]  = rest.to_s.split(/\s*,\s*/).reject(&:empty?); respond "[grinsawl] want: #{state[:want].join(', ')}"
      when 'avoid' then state[:avoid] = rest.to_s.split(/\s*,\s*/).reject(&:empty?); respond "[grinsawl] avoid: #{state[:avoid].join(', ')}"
      when 'scan', 'rescan'
        # Both rebuild the cache from scratch: walk the whole tome AND re-read the
        # card pack (loose cards), so counts reflect reality in both places.
        state[:scan_tome_request] = true
        state[:scan_sack_request] = true
        respond "[grinsawl] rescanning your #{tome_label} and #{sack_label} from scratch..."
      when 'store'
        state[:store_request] = (rest.to_s =~ /all/i ? :all : :foiled)
        respond "[grinsawl] store (#{state[:store_request]}) queued..."
      when 'organize', 'organizer', 'org'
        state[:org_open_request] = true
        respond '[grinsawl] opening the organizer...'
      when 'clean'
        state[:clean_request] = true
        respond '[grinsawl] clean queued...'
      when 'retrieve', 'get', 'pull'
        if rest.to_s.strip.empty?
          respond '[grinsawl] usage: grinsawl retrieve [bronze|silver|gold|card] <creature>'
        else
          state[:retrieve_request] = rest.to_s.strip
          respond "[grinsawl] retrieve queued: #{rest.strip}"
        end
      when 'dump'
        respond "[grinsawl] tome: #{state[:tome_name].inspect} id=#{state[:tome_id].inspect} scanned_at=#{state[:tome_scanned_at].inspect}"
        respond "[grinsawl] card sack: #{state[:card_sack_name].inspect} id=#{state[:card_sack_id].inspect}; resolves now? #{!tome.nil?}/#{!card_sack.nil?}"
        respond "[grinsawl] tome_cards (#{tome_cards.size}): #{tome_cards.first(8).map { |c| "#{c[:creature]}/#{c[:foil] || 'none'}" }.join(', ')}"
        respond "[grinsawl] sack ledger (#{ledger.size}): #{ledger.values.first(8).map { |v| "#{v[:creature]}/#{v[:foil] || 'none'}" }.join(', ')}"
        sc = sack_contents
        respond "[grinsawl] sack LIVE contents: #{sc.size} item(s), #{sc.count { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }} grinsawl(s); GameObj.containers loaded? #{!card_sack.nil? && GameObj.containers[card_sack.id].is_a?(Array)}"
      when 'stop'  then state[:active] = false; respond '[grinsawl] stopped (idle).'
      when 'clear' then self.goal = nil; state[:active] = false; state[:byproducts] = 0; state[:config_dirty] = true; respond '[grinsawl] goal cleared.'
      else respond "[grinsawl] unknown sub-command '#{cmd}'. try: grinsawl status"
      end
    end

    def self.print_status
      if goal
        odds = state[:vangaris] && state[:vangaris][:tier]
        respond "[grinsawl] goal: #{goal[:min]}#{goal[:min] == :cap ? '' : '+'} #{goal[:creature]} | stock #{stock}/#{state[:buffer]} | bad foils #{state[:byproducts]} | vissi tier #{odds || '?'}"
      else
        respond '[grinsawl] no goal set. ;grinsawl <bronze|silver|gold> <creature>'
      end
      respond "[grinsawl] cooldowns: capture #{cd_left(:aversaris)}s, foil #{cd_left(:vangaris)}s | verbs cap=#{cap_verb} foil=#{foil_verb} | #{state[:active] ? 'ACTIVE' : 'idle'}"
      respond "[grinsawl] want: #{state[:want].join(', ')} | avoid: #{state[:avoid].join(', ')} | sack: #{state[:sack_name]}"
    end

    # ---- in-game status window (dynamic dialog, like esslevel -- no GTK) ----
    def self.window_id = 'Grinsawl'

    def self.open_window
      puts("<closeDialog id='#{window_id}'/><openDialog type='dynamic' id='#{window_id}' " \
           "title='Grinsawl' target='#{window_id}' scroll='manual' location='main' justify='3' " \
           "height='340' resident='true'><dialogData id='#{window_id}'></dialogData></openDialog>")
    end

    def self.close_window
      puts("<closeDialog id='#{window_id}'/>")
    end

    def self.sanitize(v)
      v.to_s.gsub('&', '&amp;').gsub('<', '&lt;').gsub('>', '&gt;').gsub("'", '&apos;').gsub('"', '&quot;')
    end

    # Capitalize the first letter (creatures/tiers read nicer in the window).
    def self.cap(s) = s.to_s.sub(/\A([a-z])/) { Regexp.last_match(1).upcase }

    # Candidate target creatures for the panel: present in room UNION tracked.
    def self.target_candidates
      Summary.target_candidates(present_objs.map { |o| Match.normalize(o.name) },
                                inventory_entries, state[:want], state[:avoid])
    end

    # Each element: { kind: :label|:link, text:, cmd: (links only), left:, top: }.
    def self.status_elements
      els = []
      row = 0
      lbl = ->(t, l = 0) { els << { kind: :label, text: t, left: l, top: row * 18 } }
      lnk = ->(t, c, l)  { els << { kind: :link,  text: t, cmd: c, left: l, top: row * 18 } }

      lbl.call("Grinsawl #{VERSION}"); lnk.call('[Setup]', 'grinsawl view setup', 250); row += 1
      gtxt = goal ? "Goal: #{goal[:min] == :cap ? 'CAP-ONLY' : goal[:min].to_s.upcase} #{cap(goal[:creature])}" : 'Goal: (pick a target below)'
      lbl.call(gtxt); row += 1 # goal on its own line so long names never push the button off-screen
      btn = state[:active] ? '[Stop]' : '[Start]' # Stop just pauses (keeps the goal); centered below the goal
      lnk.call(btn, state[:active] ? 'grinsawl stop' : 'grinsawl go', [(300 - (btn.length * 6)) / 2, 0].max); row += 1
      lbl.call("Spares #{stock}/#{state[:buffer]}    Bad foils #{state[:byproducts]}    vissi Tier #{(state[:vangaris] || {})[:tier] || '?'}"); row += 1
      lbl.call("Capture: #{ready?(:aversaris) ? 'ready' : "#{cd_left(:aversaris)}s"}     Foil: #{ready?(:vangaris) ? 'ready' : "#{cd_left(:vangaris)}s"}"); row += 1
      lbl.call('Foil:') # foil floor; "Cap only" = capture, never foil. ** marks the selection.
      sel = (goal ? goal[:min] : state[:default_min])
      fx = 36
      [[:cap, 'Cap only'], [:bronze, 'Bronze'], [:silver, 'Silver'], [:gold, 'Gold']].each do |t, name|
        txt = (t == sel ? "**#{name}**" : name)
        lnk.call(txt, "grinsawl min #{t}", fx)
        fx += (txt.length * 6) + 8 # chain tightly so all four fit on one line
      end
      row += 1
      lbl.call('Target (click to set):'); row += 1
      cands = target_candidates.first(8)
      if cands.empty?
        lbl.call(' (no creatures here or tracked)'); row += 1
      else
        cands.each do |c|
          # "DONE" = you already own a gold of this one, so no need to capture it.
          label = " #{cap(c[:creature])} #{Summary.foil_tag(c[:counts])}#{c[:done] ? '  DONE' : ''}".rstrip
          lnk.call(label, "grinsawl target #{c[:creature]}", 12); row += 1
        end
      end
      # Store foiled / Store all / Organize tome share one tightly-spaced row
      # (monospace: ~6 px/char + a 10 px gap); Rescan gets its own line below.
      bx = 0
      [['[Store foiled]', 'grinsawl store'], ['[Store all]', 'grinsawl store all'],
       ['[Organize tome]', 'grinsawl organize']].each do |label, cmd|
        lnk.call(label, cmd, bx)
        bx += (label.length * 6) + 10
      end
      row += 1
      lnk.call('[Rescan for cards]', 'grinsawl rescan', 0); row += 1
      entries = inventory_entries
      totals = Hash.new(0)
      entries.each { |e| totals[e[:foil] || :unfoiled] += 1 }
      ctag = Summary.foil_tag(totals) # whole-collection total, e.g. (2G|3S|1B|4W)
      lnk.call(state[:fold_collection] ? '[+]' : '[-]', 'grinsawl fold collection', 0)
      lbl.call("Collection#{ctag.empty? ? '' : " #{ctag}"}:", 32); row += 1
      unless state[:fold_collection]
        tr = Summary.by_creature(entries)
        if tr.empty?
          lbl.call(" (nothing tracked -- capture, or scan your #{tome_label} in Setup)"); row += 1
        else
          tr.sort_by { |c, _| c }.each do |c, h| # list ALL tracked creatures (collapse to hide)
            lbl.call(" #{cap(c)} #{Summary.foil_tag(h)}".rstrip); row += 1
          end
        end
      end
      groups = Summary.group_tome(tome_cards)
      unless groups.empty?
        lnk.call(state[:fold_retrieve] ? '[+]' : '[-]', 'grinsawl fold retrieve', 0)
        lbl.call('Retrieve cards:', 32); row += 1
        unless state[:fold_retrieve]
          groups.each do |g| # list every retrievable group (collapse to hide)
            tierword = g[:foil] ? g[:foil].to_s : 'card'
            tag = Summary.foil_tag((g[:foil] || :unfoiled) => g[:qty]) # e.g. (3G) or (2X)
            lnk.call(" #{cap(g[:creature])} #{tag}".rstrip, "grinsawl retrieve #{tierword} #{g[:creature]}", 12); row += 1
          end
        end
      end
      els
    end

    def self.setup_elements
      els = []
      row = 0
      lbl = ->(t, l = 0) { els << { kind: :label, text: t, left: l, top: row * 18 } }
      lnk = ->(t, c, l)  { els << { kind: :link,  text: t, cmd: c, left: l, top: row * 18 } }

      # The panel font is monospace; `after` places a control right after a label
      # (CW px per char, +1 char gap), so [remove]/toggles sit next to their text
      # instead of floating off at a fixed column.
      cw = 6
      after = ->(t, base = 0) { base + ((t.length + 1) * cw) }

      lbl.call("Grinsawl Setup  v#{VERSION}"); lnk.call('[Done]', 'grinsawl view status', 250); row += 1 # [Done] stays right-aligned
      # Card container + card book: name + [remove] right after it when set, else a
      # click-to-set link (hold the item in a hand first).
      if state[:card_sack_name]
        t = "Card container: #{state[:card_sack_name]}"
        lbl.call(t); lnk.call('[remove]', 'grinsawl setsack none', after.call(t)); row += 1
      else
        lbl.call('Card container:'); lnk.call('[hold an item and click to set]', 'grinsawl setsack hand', after.call('Card container:')); row += 1
      end
      if state[:tome_name]
        t = "Card book: #{state[:tome_name]}"
        lbl.call(t); lnk.call('[remove]', 'grinsawl settome none', after.call(t)); row += 1
      else
        lbl.call('Card book:'); lnk.call('[hold an item and click to set]', 'grinsawl settome hand', after.call('Card book:')); row += 1
      end
      row += 1
      lbl.call(state[:tome_scanned_at] ? "Scanned: #{tome_cards.size} card(s) on file." : 'Not scanned yet (filed cards uncounted).'); row += 1
      lnk.call('[rescan tome + pack]', 'grinsawl rescan', 12); row += 1
      row += 1
      lbl.call("Tome stack per slot: #{state[:tome_cap]}"); row += 1
      lnk.call('[auto-detect from tome]', 'grinsawl tometier', 12); row += 1
      row += 1
      st = "Disabling spell: #{state[:disable_spell].to_s.empty? ? '(unset)' : state[:disable_spell]}"
      lbl.call(st)
      lnk.call(state[:disable_enabled] ? '[Turn Off]' : '[Turn On]', state[:disable_enabled] ? 'grinsawl spell off' : 'grinsawl spell on', after.call(st)); row += 1
      lbl.call('  set with  ;grinsawl spell <number>'); row += 1
      row += 1
      mm = state[:max_mobs].to_i
      mlabel = 'Pause when monsters exceed:'
      val = mm.zero? ? 'off' : mm.to_s
      mx = after.call(mlabel)    # [-]
      vx = after.call('[-]', mx) # value, one char after [-]
      lbl.call(mlabel)
      lnk.call('[-]', "grinsawl maxmobs #{[mm - 1, 0].max}", mx)
      lbl.call(val, vx)
      lnk.call('[+]', "grinsawl maxmobs #{mm + 1}", after.call(val, vx)); row += 1
      apt = 'Auto-pause when not standing:'
      lbl.call(apt)
      lnk.call(state[:pause_not_standing] ? '[Turn Off]' : '[Turn On]', 'grinsawl standpause', after.call(apt)); row += 1
      row += 1
      lbl.call('Scripts paused during capture/foil:'); row += 1
      if state[:pause_list].empty?
        lbl.call('  (none)', 12); row += 1
      else
        state[:pause_list].each do |n|
          lbl.call(n, 12)
          lnk.call('[remove]', "grinsawl unpause #{n}", after.call(n, 12)); row += 1
        end
      end
      lbl.call('  add with  ;grinsawl pause <name>'); row += 1
      els
    end

    def self.render_window
      els = state[:view] == :setup ? setup_elements : status_elements
      out = +"<dialogData id='#{window_id}' clear='t' >"
      els.each_with_index do |e, i|
        out << if e[:kind] == :link
                 "<link id='gl_#{i}' value='#{sanitize(e[:text])}' cmd='#{sanitize(e[:cmd])}' echo='#{sanitize(e[:cmd])}' justify='left' left='#{e[:left]}' top='#{e[:top]}' />"
               else
                 "<label id='gl_#{i}' value='#{sanitize(e[:text])}' justify='left' left='#{e[:left]}' top='#{e[:top]}' />"
               end
      end
      out << '</dialogData>'
      puts(out)
    rescue StandardError => e
      respond "[grinsawl] window error: #{e.message}" if state[:debug]
    end

    # ============================ ORGANIZER (Phase 4) =========================
    # A GTK window to arrange the tome to a target layout. Editing happens in the GTK thread
    # (Gtk.queue); Send/Rebuild/Rescan push intents onto state[:org_queue] which the MAIN
    # LOOP drains (all game I/O on the script thread, like store/retrieve).
    def self.gtk_ready? = defined?(Gtk) && Gtk.respond_to?(:queue)

    # Cards (each { leaf, slot, creature, foil, qty }) + a leaf count -> 0-indexed layout:
    # layout[leaf_i][slot_i] = list of 0-2 cards { creature:, foil: }. The count is clamped
    # up to the highest leaf actually present so no card is ever dropped.
    def self.build_layout(cards, nleaves)
      cards = Array(cards)
      n = [nleaves.to_i, cards.map { |c| c[:leaf].to_i }.max.to_i, 1].max
      layout = Array.new(n) { Array.new(12) { [] } }
      cards.each do |c|
        li = c[:leaf].to_i - 1
        si = c[:slot].to_i - 1
        next unless li >= 0 && si.between?(0, 11)

        [c[:qty].to_i, 1].max.times { layout[li][si] << { creature: c[:creature], foil: c[:foil] } }
      end
      layout
    end

    # Re-read ONLY the given leaves into the cache (organize touches just a few leaves, so
    # this avoids the full 12-leaf walk). Replaces those leaves' entries in tome_cards.
    def self.rescan_leaves(t, leaves)
      want = Array(leaves).map(&:to_i).uniq
      return if want.empty?

      state[:tome_cards] = tome_cards.reject { |c| want.include?(c[:leaf].to_i) }
      want.each do |ln|
        next unless goto_leaf(t, ln)

        insp = tome_io("inspect ##{t.id}", /open leaf|thumb your fingers|\bleaf\b|empty slot|grinsawl|study/i)
        Grinsawl::Tome.leaf(insp)[:slots].each { |sl| state[:tome_cards] << sl.merge(leaf: ln) if sl }
      end
      state[:tome_scanned_at] = Time.now.to_i
    end

    # Drop any ledger entry that is not physically loose (sack or a hand) -- e.g. a card
    # the organizer just filed -- so it is not double-counted against the rebuilt tome
    # cache (loose sack ids and ephemeral tome ids never match, so dedup can't catch it).
    def self.reconcile_loose_ledger
      ensure_sack_loaded
      here = (sack_contents + held).map { |o| o.id.to_s }
      ledger.keys.each { |id| ledger.delete(id) unless here.include?(id) }
    end

    def self.open_organizer
      return respond('[grinsawl] the organizer needs GTK3, which is not available in this Lich.') unless gtk_ready?

      t = tome
      return respond("[grinsawl] no #{tome_label} assigned -- set it in Setup first.") unless t
      return respond('[grinsawl] the organizer is already open.') if state[:organizer]

      detect_tome_tier # ANALYZE: per-slot cap + leaf count (also lets us skip a full walk)
      # Open from the cached layout -- grinsawl keeps it current as it captures/foils/stores
      # /organizes. Only walk the whole tome if we have no scan at all. Rescan refreshes; a
      # stale cache surfaces as a miss during organize (which then suggests Rescan).
      if tome_cards.empty? && !state[:tome_scanned_at]
        respond "[grinsawl] opening the organizer (first scan of #{t.name})..."
        scan_tome_into_cache(t)
      else
        respond "[grinsawl] opening the organizer for #{t.name} (from the last scan -- Rescan to refresh)."
      end
      layout = build_layout(tome_cards, state[:tome_leaves])
      q = (state[:org_queue] ||= Queue.new)
      cap = state[:tome_cap]
      Gtk.queue do
        state[:organizer] = OrgWindow.new(q, layout, tome_label, cap)
        state[:organizer].show_all
      end
    end

    # Drain organizer intents (main loop, script thread).
    def self.organizer_drain
      q = state[:org_queue]
      return unless q

      until q.empty?
        intent = (q.pop(true) rescue nil)
        break unless intent

        case intent[:action]
        when :organize then organize_execute(intent[:plan])
        when :rescan   then respond '[grinsawl] organizer: full rescan...'; refresh_organizer
        when :close    then state[:organizer] = nil; respond '[grinsawl] organizer closed.'
        end
      end
    end

    # Push a fresh scan back into the open window. only: a list of leaf numbers re-reads
    # just those (fast, after an organize); nil walks the whole tome (the Rescan button).
    def self.refresh_organizer(only: nil)
      win = state[:organizer]
      return unless win && gtk_ready?

      t = tome or return

      if only && !Array(only).empty?
        rescan_leaves(t, only)
        reconcile_loose_ledger
        save_tome_cache
      else
        scan_tome_into_cache(t) # full walk (Rescan button)
      end
      layout = build_layout(tome_cards, state[:tome_leaves])
      Gtk.queue { win.load_current(layout) rescue nil }
    end

    # A sack grinsawl whose type matches (creature, foil), or nil.
    def self.find_sack_card(creature, foil)
      sack_contents.select { |o| o.name.to_s =~ /grinsawl/i }.each do |o|
        info = ledger[o.id.to_s] || look_card(o.id) || {}
        ledger[o.id.to_s] = info if info[:creature]
        return { id: o.id.to_s, creature: info[:creature], foil: info[:foil] } \
          if info[:creature] && Match.identical?(info[:creature], creature) && info[:foil] == foil
      end
      nil
    end

    # Run an organizer plan: lift the misplaced cards out to the sack (PULL), then file the
    # vacancies from the sack (FILL). Reuses retrieve/store primitives and the ledger-held
    # rule; with_tome_hands sets aside the user's gear and restores it. Then rescans.
    def self.organize_execute(plan)
      t = tome
      return respond("[grinsawl] no #{tome_label} to organize.") unless t

      pulls = Array(plan && plan[:pull])
      fills = Array(plan && plan[:fill])
      return respond('[grinsawl] organizer: nothing to change.') if pulls.empty? && fills.empty?

      respond "[grinsawl] organizing #{t.name}: lifting #{pulls.size}, filing #{fills.size}..."
      filed = 0
      aborted = false
      stale = false # a card the cache expected wasn't there -> the cache is out of date
      with_pause do
        ensure_sack_loaded
        # Hold the LEDGER in hand for the WHOLE operation (filing needs it held). with_tome_hands
        # frees both hands of the user's gear up front and restores it afterward.
        with_tome_hands(t) do |ok|
        unless ok
          respond "[grinsawl] organizer: couldn't get your #{t.name} in hand -- aborting."
          aborted = true
          next
        end
        state[:cur_leaf] = nil # grabbing the ledger may have moved it; re-establish once
        # PULL: lift each misplaced card out to the sack (ledger stays in one hand, the
        # lifted card goes to the other, then to the sack).
        pulls.each do |(leaf, slot)|
          next unless goto_leaf(t, leaf)

          insp = tome_io("inspect ##{t.id}", /open leaf|thumb your fingers|\bleaf\b|empty slot|grinsawl|study/i)
          cell = (Grinsawl::Tome.leaf(insp)[:slots] || [])[slot.to_i - 1]
          unless cell && cell[:id]
            stale = true # cache said a card was here, but the slot is empty
            next
          end

          free_hand! # free the non-ledger hand for the lifted card
          tome_io("get ##{cell[:id]}", /separates cleanly|don't|can't|isn't|no .*grinsawl|not your|Get what/i)
          g = nil
          15.times { g = held_grinsawl; break if g; sleep 0.1 } # GameObj hand updates async
          if g
            ledger[g.id.to_s] = { creature: cell[:creature], foil: cell[:foil] }
            stow_to_sack(g.id)
          end
        end
        # FILL: file vacancies from the sack (ledger still held).
        ensure_sack_loaded
        fills.each do |f|
          card = find_sack_card(f[:creature], f[:foil])
          unless card
            respond "[grinsawl] organizer: out of #{f[:foil] || 'unfoiled'} #{f[:creature]} cards to file."
            stale = true # cache expected this card to be available
            next
          end
          next unless get_from_sack(card[:id])
          next unless goto_leaf(t, f[:leaf])

          res = tome_io("tap ##{t.id} at #{f[:slot]}", /grafted likeness remains|join|combine|already|can't|full|no room|doesn't match|What were you/i)
          if store_took?(res, card[:id])
            ledger.delete(card[:id]) # filed now -- drop it from the loose ledger (no double count)
            filed += 1
          end
        end
        end # with_tome_hands (stows the tome + restores the user's gear)
      end
      return if aborted
      # Only the touched leaves changed, so re-read just those (not the whole tome).
      affected = (pulls.map { |(l, _s)| l.to_i } + fills.map { |f| f[:leaf].to_i }).uniq
      respond "[grinsawl] organizer: filed #{filed} card(s); rescanning leaf/leaves #{affected.sort.join(', ')}..."
      respond "[grinsawl] some cards weren't where expected -- your #{tome_label} view was out of date. Click [Rescan] for a fresh read." if stale
      refresh_organizer(only: affected)
    end

    # Foil -> text/border color. Unfoiled and empty get muted greys.
    FOIL_COLORS = { gold: '#d4af37', silver: '#c0c0c0', bronze: '#cd7f32' }.freeze

    if defined?(Gtk) && Gtk.respond_to?(:queue)
      # One tome slot button. The foil reads at a glance two ways: the tier is its own
      # colored top line (above the creature name), and the box gets a thick border in the
      # tier's color (via a CSS class -- see OrgWindow#install_css).
      class OrgSlot < Gtk::Button
        def initialize(idx, on_click)
          super()
          @idx = idx
          @label = Gtk::Label.new
          @label.set_use_markup(true)
          @label.set_line_wrap(true)
          @label.set_justify(:center)
          add(@label)
          set_size_request(132, 78)
          (style_context.add_class('grinsawl-slot') rescue nil) # scopes our border CSS to slots only
          signal_connect('clicked') { on_click.call(@idx) }
        end

        def render(cards, differs, editable)
          cards = Array(cards)
          set_foil_class(cards.empty? ? 'empty' : (cards.first[:foil] || 'none').to_s)
          head = "<b>#{@idx + 1}.</b>"
          body = if cards.empty?
                   "#{head} <i>empty</i>"
                 else
                   c = cards.first
                   color = Grinsawl::FOIL_COLORS[c[:foil]] || '#bbbbbb'
                   tier  = c[:foil] ? c[:foil].to_s.capitalize : 'Unfoiled'
                   qty   = cards.size > 1 ? " (x#{cards.size})" : ''
                   # tier on its own colored line, creature name below
                   "#{head} <span foreground='#{color}'><b>#{tier}</b></span>#{qty}\n#{esc(c[:creature])}"
                 end
          # green wash marks a slot that differs from current (only meaningful in target view)
          @label.set_markup((differs && editable) ? "<span background='#cfe9c4' foreground='#000000'>#{body}</span>" : body)
        end

        # Swap the foil-* CSS class so the border color tracks the tier (see install_css).
        def set_foil_class(tier)
          ctx = style_context
          %w[gold silver bronze none empty].each { |c| ctx.remove_class("foil-#{c}") }
          ctx.add_class("foil-#{tier}")
        rescue StandardError
          nil
        end

        def esc(s) = s.to_s.gsub('&', '&amp;').gsub('<', '&lt;').gsub('>', '&gt;')
      end

      # The organizer window: one leaf at a time, a Held tray for cross-leaf moves.
      class OrgWindow < Gtk::Window
        def initialize(queue, layout, tome_label, cap = 2)
          super("Grinsawl Organizer -- #{tome_label}")
          @queue = queue
          @tome_label = tome_label
          @cap = [cap.to_i, 1].max
          @current = deep(layout)
          @target  = deep(layout)
          @nleaves = [Array(layout).size, 1].max
          @leaf = 0
          @viewing_current = false
          @held = nil
          @undo = []
          set_default_size(580, 480)
          signal_connect('destroy') { @queue.push(action: :close) }
          install_css
          build_ui
          refresh
        end

        # A thick border per foil tier on each slot box (CSS classes the slots toggle).
        def install_css
          css = +'.grinsawl-slot { border-width: 3px; border-style: solid; border-radius: 4px; }'
          { 'gold' => Grinsawl::FOIL_COLORS[:gold], 'silver' => Grinsawl::FOIL_COLORS[:silver],
            'bronze' => Grinsawl::FOIL_COLORS[:bronze], 'none' => '#888888', 'empty' => '#555555' }.each do |k, c|
            style = k == 'empty' ? 'dashed' : 'solid'
            css << " .grinsawl-slot.foil-#{k} { border-color: #{c}; border-style: #{style}; }"
          end
          provider = Gtk::CssProvider.new
          provider.load(data: css)
          Gtk::StyleContext.add_provider_for_screen(Gdk::Screen.default, provider, Gtk::StyleProvider::PRIORITY_APPLICATION)
        rescue StandardError
          nil # CSS borders are a nicety; the colored tier line still conveys the foil
        end

        def deep(layout) = Array(layout).map { |lf| Array(lf).map { |sl| Array(sl).map(&:dup) } }

        def shown = @viewing_current ? @current : @target

        def build_ui
          vbox = Gtk::Box.new(:vertical, 6)
          vbox.margin = 8
          add(vbox)

          top = Gtk::Box.new(:horizontal, 6)
          @view_toggle = Gtk::ToggleButton.new(label: 'Show current (read-only)')
          @view_toggle.signal_connect('toggled') do
            @viewing_current = @view_toggle.active?
            @view_toggle.label = @viewing_current ? 'Show target (editable)' : 'Show current (read-only)'
            refresh
          end
          top.pack_start(@view_toggle, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)
          top.pack_start(Gtk::Label.new(''), expand: true, fill: true, padding: 0)
          @prev_btn = Gtk::Button.new(label: '<')
          @prev_btn.signal_connect('clicked') { @leaf = (@leaf - 1) % @nleaves; refresh }
          @leaf_label = Gtk::Label.new
          @next_btn = Gtk::Button.new(label: '>')
          @next_btn.signal_connect('clicked') { @leaf = (@leaf + 1) % @nleaves; refresh }
          top.pack_start(@prev_btn, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)
          top.pack_start(@leaf_label, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)
          top.pack_start(@next_btn, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)
          vbox.pack_start(top, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)

          @held_label = Gtk::Label.new
          @held_label.set_use_markup(true)
          @held_label.set_xalign(0.0)
          vbox.pack_start(@held_label, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)

          @grid = Gtk::Grid.new
          @grid.column_spacing = 6
          @grid.row_spacing = 6
          @slots = (0...12).map do |i|
            w = OrgSlot.new(i, method(:on_click))
            @grid.attach(w, i % 4, i / 4, 1, 1)
            w
          end
          vbox.pack_start(@grid, expand: true, fill: true, padding: 0)

          @status = Gtk::Label.new
          @status.set_use_markup(true)
          @status.set_xalign(0.0)
          vbox.pack_start(@status, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)

          btns = Gtk::Box.new(:horizontal, 6)
          [['Send to game', :send], ['Undo', :undo], ['Reset', :reset],
           ['Rebuild', :rebuild], ['Rescan', :rescan], ['Close', :close]].each do |label, act|
            b = Gtk::Button.new(label: label)
            b.signal_connect('clicked') { on_button(act) }
            btns.pack_start(b, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)
          end
          vbox.pack_start(btns, expand: false, fill: false, padding: 0)
        end

        def on_click(i)
          if @viewing_current
            set_status('Current is read-only -- press "Show target (editable)" to edit.', '#ffaa44')
            return
          end
          cell = @target[@leaf][i]
          if @held.nil?
            return if cell.empty?

            snapshot
            @held = cell.pop
          elsif cell.empty?
            snapshot
            cell.push(@held)
            @held = nil
          elsif same?(cell.first, @held)
            if cell.size < @cap
              snapshot
              cell.push(@held)
              @held = nil
            else
              set_status("That stack is full (#{@cap} per slot).", '#ffaa44')
              return
            end
          elsif cell.size == 1
            snapshot
            displaced = cell.pop
            cell.push(@held)
            @held = displaced
          else
            set_status('That slot holds a stack of another card.', '#ffaa44')
            return
          end
          refresh
        end

        def same?(a, b) = a && b && a[:creature].to_s == b[:creature].to_s && a[:foil] == b[:foil]

        def snapshot
          @undo << [deep(@target), @held && @held.dup]
          @undo.shift if @undo.size > 50
        end

        def on_button(act)
          case act
          when :undo
            if @undo.empty?
              set_status('Nothing to undo.', '#88bbff')
            else
              @target, @held = @undo.pop
              refresh
            end
          when :reset
            snapshot
            @target = deep(@current)
            @held = nil
            set_status('Target reset to current.', '#88bbff')
            refresh
          when :rescan
            set_status('Rescanning the tome...', '#d4af37')
            @queue.push(action: :rescan)
          when :close
            destroy
          when :send, :rebuild
            return set_status('Drop the held card into a slot before sending.', '#ffaa44') if @held

            plan = Grinsawl::Tome::Plan.plan(@current, @target, full: (act == :rebuild))
            return set_status('Already matches the tome; nothing to do.', '#88bbff') if plan[:pull].empty? && plan[:fill].empty?

            set_status("Queued: lift #{plan[:pull].size}, file #{plan[:fill].size}...", '#d4af37')
            @queue.push(action: :organize, plan: plan)
          end
        end

        # Called from the worker (via Gtk.queue) after execute / rescan.
        def load_current(layout)
          @current = deep(layout)
          @target  = deep(layout)
          @held = nil
          @undo = []
          @nleaves = [Array(layout).size, 1].max
          @leaf = [[@leaf, 0].max, @nleaves - 1].min
          set_status('Updated from a fresh scan.', '#88bbff')
          refresh
        end

        def refresh
          @leaf_label.set_text(" Leaf #{@leaf + 1} / #{@nleaves} ")
          h = @held ? "#{(@held[:foil] || 'unfoiled').to_s.capitalize} #{@held[:creature]}" : '(nothing)'
          @held_label.set_markup("Held: <b>#{esc(h)}</b>   (click a card to pick up, a slot to drop)")
          lay = shown
          @slots.each_with_index do |w, i|
            differs = !@viewing_current && !same_cell?(@current.dig(@leaf, i), @target.dig(@leaf, i))
            w.render(lay.dig(@leaf, i), differs, !@viewing_current)
          end
          show_all
        rescue StandardError
          nil
        end

        def same_cell?(a, b)
          Array(a).map { |c| [c[:creature].to_s, c[:foil]] }.sort_by(&:to_s) ==
            Array(b).map { |c| [c[:creature].to_s, c[:foil]] }.sort_by(&:to_s)
        end

        def esc(s) = s.to_s.gsub('&', '&amp;').gsub('<', '&lt;').gsub('>', '&gt;')

        def set_status(msg, color = '#cccccc')
          @status.set_markup("<span foreground='#{color}'>#{esc(msg)}</span>")
        end
      end
    end

    # ---- main tick ----
    # While dead: announce once and drop queued game-I/O so nothing fires as a ghost or on
    # revival. The capture/foil loop is gated in tick and resumes on its own.
    def self.pause_for_death
      unless state[:dead_noted]
        respond '[grinsawl] you are dead -- capture/foil and tome work are paused until you are back.'
        state[:dead_noted] = true
      end
      state[:scan_tome_request] = false
      state[:scan_sack_request] = false
      state[:store_request] = nil
      state[:retrieve_request] = nil
      state[:org_open_request] = false
      state[:detect_tier_request] = false
      (state[:org_queue].clear rescue nil) if state[:org_queue]
    end

    # On revival: announce once and finish any setup (arcaria analyze) skipped while dead.
    def self.resume_after_death
      return unless state[:dead_noted]

      state[:dead_noted] = false
      respond '[grinsawl] back among the living -- resuming.'
      analyze_arcaria if state[:need_analyze]
    end

    def self.tick
      return if dead?
      return unless state[:active] && goal && configured?

      objs  = present_objs
      names = objs.map { |o| Match.normalize(o.name) }.reject(&:empty?).uniq
      base  = { goal: goal, present: names, unfoiled_creatures: unfoiled_goal_creatures,
                stock: stock, buffer: state[:buffer] }

      # Would grinsawl act on anything here if nothing were in the way? (cooldowns
      # forced ready). If not, stay SILENT -- no pause / cooldown / heads-up chatter
      # unless we'd otherwise be doing something. So the "paused: you're prone"
      # message only fires once a targeted creature is actually present, etc.
      foil_pending    = Planner.next_action(base.merge(vangaris_ready: true,  aversaris_ready: false)).is_a?(Array)
      capture_pending = Planner.next_action(base.merge(vangaris_ready: false, aversaris_ready: true)).is_a?(Array)
      unless foil_pending || capture_pending
        state[:paused_reason] = nil # nothing here to resume to; clear quietly
        return
      end

      # There IS a target we'd work on -- now safety holds are worth announcing.
      if (reason = pause_reason)
        note_paused(reason)
        return
      end
      note_resumed

      # Count down only the activation(s) that actually have a target waiting.
      relevant = []
      relevant << :vangaris  if foil_pending
      relevant << :aversaris if capture_pending
      announce_cooldowns(relevant)

      action = Planner.next_action(base.merge(aversaris_ready: ready?(:aversaris), vangaris_ready: ready?(:vangaris)))
      return unless action.is_a?(Array) # on cooldown -> the countdown above already spoke

      kind, name = action
      obj = objs.find { |o| Match.normalize(o.name) == name }
      return unless obj

      # Heads-up + grace period so you can weave your own hunting around it.
      respond ">>> [grinsawl] #{kind == :foil ? 'FOILING' : 'CAPTURING'} #{cap(name)} in #{WARN_SECS} seconds <<<"
      sleep WARN_SECS
      kind == :foil ? do_foil(obj) : do_capture(obj)
    end
  end

  $VERBOSE = $grinsawl_prior_verbose # finished defining constants; restore normal warnings

  Grinsawl.boot
  Grinsawl.setup
  Grinsawl.open_window

  if (args = Script.current.vars[1..].to_a.join(' ').strip) && !args.empty?
    Grinsawl.set_goal(args)
  else
    respond "[grinsawl v#{Grinsawl.version}] ready. Set a goal: ;grinsawl <bronze|silver|gold> <creature>"
  end

  UpstreamHook.add('grinsawl', proc do |cmd|
    begin
      if (m = /\A(?:<c>)?\s*grinsawl\b\s*(.*)\z/i.match(cmd))
        Grinsawl.handle_command(m[1])
        next nil
      end
    rescue StandardError => e
      respond "[grinsawl] command error: #{e.message}"
    end
    cmd
  end)

  # Watch the game stream for a thrown-away grinsawl ("...you cast it aside") and queue
  # it; the main loop drops it from the collection so counts stay right without a rescan.
  DownstreamHook.add('grinsawl', proc do |line|
    begin
      if (d = Grinsawl::Parse.discard(line)) && Grinsawl.state && Grinsawl.state[:discarded]
        Grinsawl.state[:discarded] << d
      end
    rescue StandardError
      nil
    end
    line
  end)

  before_dying do
    UpstreamHook.remove('grinsawl')
    DownstreamHook.remove('grinsawl')
    Grinsawl.persist_config if Grinsawl.state # flush config (before_dying runs on the script thread)
    if Grinsawl.state && Grinsawl.state[:organizer] && Grinsawl.gtk_ready?
      Gtk.queue { Grinsawl.state[:organizer]&.destroy rescue nil } rescue nil
    end
    Grinsawl.close_window
    respond '[grinsawl] stopped.'
  end

  loop do
    begin
      if Grinsawl.dead?
        Grinsawl.pause_for_death # ghost: skip ALL game I/O until revived
      else
        Grinsawl.resume_after_death
        if (dq = Grinsawl.state[:discarded]) # cards thrown away -> drop from the collection live
          until dq.empty?
            d = (dq.pop(true) rescue nil) or break
            respond "[grinsawl] tossed a #{d[:foil] || 'white'} #{Grinsawl.cap(d[:creature])}; removed from your collection." if Grinsawl.remove_loose(d[:creature], d[:foil])
          end
        end
        if Grinsawl.state[:scan_tome_request]
          Grinsawl.state[:scan_tome_request] = false
          Grinsawl.scan_tome
        end
        if Grinsawl.state[:scan_sack_request]
          Grinsawl.state[:scan_sack_request] = false
          Grinsawl.scan_sack
          respond "[grinsawl] #{Grinsawl.sack_label} scan: #{Grinsawl.ledger.size} card(s) tracked (#{Grinsawl.stock} unfoiled goal)."
        end
        if (req = Grinsawl.state[:store_request])
          Grinsawl.state[:store_request] = nil
          Grinsawl.store_cards(req)
        end
        if (req = Grinsawl.state[:retrieve_request])
          Grinsawl.state[:retrieve_request] = nil
          Grinsawl.run_retrieve(req)
        end
        if Grinsawl.state[:clean_request]
          Grinsawl.state[:clean_request] = false
          Grinsawl.run_clean
        end
        if Grinsawl.state[:detect_tier_request]
          Grinsawl.state[:detect_tier_request] = false
          Grinsawl.detect_tome_tier
        end
        if Grinsawl.state[:org_open_request]
          Grinsawl.state[:org_open_request] = false
          Grinsawl.open_organizer
        end
        Grinsawl.organizer_drain
        Grinsawl.persist_config if Grinsawl.state[:config_dirty]
        Grinsawl.tick
      end
      Grinsawl.render_window
    rescue StandardError => e
      respond "[grinsawl] tick error: #{e.class}: #{e.message}"
    end
    sleep 1.5
  end
end

# Restore for non-runtime loads (e.g. the test harness, where the block above is skipped).
$VERBOSE = $grinsawl_prior_verbose
